title: texas pecan cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar; add eggs and lemon extract and beat. Add flour and baking powder.
Mix.
Add nuts and fruit.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and oil; add eggs (beaten) and vanilla. Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Chill; form into balls and dip in sugar.
Put on cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of glass or fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Line bottom of
pan
with bread.
Mix other ingredients in order given and
pour mixture over the bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: stay-a-bed stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large casserole with tight-fitting lid.
Place in 275° oven.
Now you can go back to bed.
It will cook all by itself and be done in five hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: garlic thyme chicken(serves 4)
directions: Prepare chicken several hours ahead:
Rub oil well into chicken with fingers, then rub in garlic, thyme, lemon juice, oregano and pepper.
Place chicken in skillet; add water.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 to 12 minutes, turning once.
Chicken should be brown on the outside and no longer pink on the inside. Serve immediately.

title: marinated porterhouse steak
directions: In a large shallow baking dish, place steak.
Pour wine over steak.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
About 40 minutes before serving, preheat broiler. Place steak on greased rack in broiling pan.
Reserve marinade. Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.
Broil 30 minutes for rare or until desired doneness, basting occasionally with marinade and turning once.

title: chocolate cake brownies
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
In a large bowl, mix flour and salt with sugar.
In a saucepan, mix cocoa, water and shortening. Bring to a boil.
Add this to flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla, soda and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 18-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with frosting.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Soften margarine a little and cream together with peanut butter.
Fold in confectioners sugar.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and place on waxed paper.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip peanut butter ball into melted chocolate, leaving a bit of the ball uncovered.
Return ball to waxed paper to cool.
This recipe makes a lot of Buckeyes, but there's never enough.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar in large mixing bowl using electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add grated carrots to mixture.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Bring to a boil cocoa, margarine and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Five minutes before cake is done, fix frosting.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt together oleo and chocolate.
Pour over sugar and add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: regular shortbread
directions: Mix; press into cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple eggnog
directions: In large bowl beat egg yolks until thick; add sugar, ice cream and apple juice.
Mix until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into apple juice mixture.
Sprinkle each serving with nutmeg.
Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: peggy's beef brisket
directions: Mix the seasoned salts and rub into all surfaces of the brisket.
Place brisket in a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Pour liquid smoke over meat and tightly seal foil.
Place in a 275° oven and bake 7 to 8 hours.
Can be baked overnight, then refrigerated until almost serving time, then reheated.
Slice across the grain and trim off fat as you slice.
Leftovers can be reheated or chopped and served with barbecue sauce as a sandwich.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large brown grocery bag; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients, except baking soda, in 1 1/2-quart glass dish.
Microwave on High until mixture boils; stir. Microwave for 2 minutes on High, stirring after each minute. Remove from microwave; stir in soda.
Pour over corn in bag. Close bag; shake well.
Microwave in bag for 1 1/2 minutes on High; shake well.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour onto countertop or table to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: kraut salad-relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and let refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
(Very important.)
The egg whites should be at room temperature.
Beat whites slowly; add sugar and salt. Fold in "bits and pieces."
Oil cookie sheets with butter or margarine.
Drop cookies with spoon.
Put in preheated oven; cut off oven and leave at least 3 hours.
May be left overnight.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread crumbs) well and pour into casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and chop mushroom stems.
Reserve.
Saute stems in garlic and butter.
Add sausage and brown.
Stir in bread crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Season to taste.
Stuff caps with 1 tablespoon filling.
Place in shallow baking dish and brush with 1 tablespoon butter.
Broil 4 inches from heat until bubbly and brown, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients as any loaf cake, using cherry juice for liquid.
If mixture seems too soft, add more flour.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in loaf or tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and syrup.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until filling is firm.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the cherries.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pan will be 3/4 full.
Top with the cherries that have been drained.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute scallions in butter; do not brown.
Add cheese and let melt.
Stuff caps and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: twice baked mashed potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Top with remaining bacon bits.

title: strawberry-carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Beat all ingredients except strawberries in a large bowl on low speed for 45 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in strawberries. Pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: walnut raisin cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add yogurt and eggs; mix together. Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda; mix.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
You may use a tablespoon of milk or more to thin the mix to the consistency you like.

title: carla's chili(car'lotta's "great chili")
directions: Chop celery.
Cut green peppers and onion into chunks.
Brown and drain ground meat.
Mix all the ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil over medium heat, then simmer on low for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix green pepper with onion and tomato.
Layer these ingredients in a shallow dish (approximately 9 inches) and serve with crackers or other dipping foods.

title: easy dinner mints
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Form into balls and flatten with fork or back of spoon, dipped in 4x sugar on wax paper.
Let dry completely.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix the taco sauce and cream cheese together.
Place mixture in pie pan or casserole dish and spread flat.
Layer the remaining ingredients on top of the cream cheese mixture, in the order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Mix all together until completely mixed.
Bake in a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Cut ham into 1/2-inch pieces; dice celery, carrots, onion and zucchini.
Remove 1 1/2 cups beans; mash beans until smooth.
In 5-quart pan over medium heat, cook ham and all veggies in hot oil. Add spices.
Cook until tender and begins to brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, chopped and squeezed spinach, mashed beans and 2 cups water, using spoon to break up tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer to blend flavors, 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining beans.
Spoon soup into large bowls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked rice and broccoli in a 2-quart casserole dish. Saute onion and celery in skillet with margarine until tender. Stir in soup and milk mixture.
Add cheese and stir thoroughly. Pour sauce over rice and broccoli in casserole.
Mix slightly. Top with crackers or Cheez-Its cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
May add a few sliced cooked carrots with broccoli (this adds color).
If you like mushrooms, add a small can (drained).
Saute with the onions and celery.

title: corn fritters
directions: Chop corn; drain.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder and paprika; stir in corn mixture.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg white; dip batter by teaspoonful and slide into heated oil with the heat control at 375°.
Fry until medium brown for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water, drain and add all other ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower
directions: Boil head of cauliflower, with green hull attached, in water for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat chicken broth, chicken soup, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Layer Doritos, chicken, soup, onion and cheese throughout.
Top with Doritos and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable beef patties
directions: Divide ground chuck in half.
Make 2 patties.
Place potatoes, carrots, onions, salt, pepper and 1 pat of butter on each.
Wrap individually in tin foil, place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 2.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Cream together next 4 ingredients. Mix together and add chocolate bits and vanilla.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter; mix with cracker crumbs.
Form a crust in the pan, then layer coconut on top of crust.
Put chips on top of it, then sprinkle pecans over chips and pour can of milk evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Add all ingredients, except diet sweetener in 8 ounces of boiling water.
Stir until dissolved and add sweetener as needed.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake on a large greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash; cook and mash.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Test for doneness by inserting fork in the center.

title: honey flavored chicken breasts and sweet potatoes(serves 4)
directions: Place sweet potato chunks and onion slices around chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered.
Then baste chicken breasts and sweet potatoes with sauce and bake another 30 minutes.
Then add peaches to the mixture altogether around everything and bake the last 15 minutes.
First, baste one more time with sauce over sweet potatoes and chicken. Serves 4 people.
Total baking time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil
chicken;	remove from broth.
Cook rice in broth. Thaw broccoli in 1 cup boiling water.
Saute celery and onions in butter until light brown.
Add soup, milk, cheese, drained, chopped
broccoli, chopped chicken, onion and celery to cooked rice.
Cook for a minute or 2 then pour into a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and put in oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool before adding other ingredients.
Mix last 5 ingredients well and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: stokley's finest pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thoroughly blend all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer; cool completely, then enjoy.

title: heloise's diet strawberry jam
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the gelatin, in saucepan.
Cook on high for 3 to 4 minutes.
Taste for tartness and, if needed, add more sugar substitute.
Sprinkle gelatin into mixture, stirring until dissolved completely.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger bean pot soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add all the rest of the ingredients except pork and beans.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Add pork and beans.
Mix well and heat through.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Cream together the shortening, sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat in thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Add black walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: hershey's fudge brownies(1994 entry)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 20 brownies.

title: morning cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth and frothy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: easy coconut cream pie(makes two 9-inch pies)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in large microwave-safe bowl.
Gradually add milk, stirring with whisk.
Microwave on High 15 minutes, stirring ever 5 minutes.
Beat yolks until frothy. Slowly add a little of hot milk mixture to yolks, then add yolk mixture back to bowl containing hot milk mixture.
Add coconut. Microwave on High 4 minutes, stirring ever 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Add margarine and coconut flavoring.
Mix well.
Cool slightly and pour into baked shells.
Top with meringue and sprinkle with flake coconut.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix chocolate pudding as directed; put in refrigerator.
Crush Oreo cookies and mix with melted margarine; press firmly in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine cream cheese, 1 Cool Whip and powdered sugar in a bowl.
Mix with an electric mixer until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of cookies.
Spread pudding on top of cream cheese mixture.
Lastly, spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in 2 quarts of water until tender. Mash well and return to heat.
Add seasonings and butter; bring to a boil.
Add hot milk.
Serve immediately with croutons.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: frozen banana pops
directions: Peel bananas; cut in half crosswise.
Insert wooden stick into each banana half.
Place on waxed paper.
Cover.
Freeze 2 hours.

title: granny's curly-roni
directions: Cook noodles until done, but not soft. Drain and set aside. Place water, milk, margarine and cheese in pan. Cook slowly, stirring until cheese melts. Add noodles and cover. Cook slowly until heated through.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, celery, scallions, green pepper, pimiento, olives and parsley in a large bowl; toss to mix.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise and vinegar until smooth.
Add to macaroni mixture. Add pepper and salt to taste.
Toss.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Saute bread cubes in lard until golden brown.
Grate potatoes; add flour, salt and eggs.
Beat mixture lightly.
Stir in bread cubes.
Mix well and form dumplings.
Cook in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Kettle should be covered during cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix together well; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine soup and mayo. Heat until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Spread bread crumbs on top and sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: cream cheese pecan cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in a greased and floured tube pan. Set aside.
Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and salt, stirring until combined.
Beat until light.
Stir in vanilla and remaining cup of pecans.
Pour batter into tube pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove.

title: on the stove hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soups and water and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and corn.
Cook on top of stove for half an hour.
Stir often.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Make batter first.
Cream the butter with 3/4 cup sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder alternately with milk; set aside.
Put berries and 1/2 cup sugar into a pan with a little water (slightly less than would cover the berries).
Bring to a boil.
Into boiling blueberry mixture, drop tablespoons of batter.
Cover pan tightly; cook over gentle heat 5 to 7 minutes. Serve immediately, topped with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger lightly in pan. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until potatoes are done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice. Mix sugar and cinnamon with apples.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, salt and melted butter.
Spread over apples.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and mix; let stand overnight.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool and add to first mixture.
Add nuts, marshmallows, chopped celery and apple.
Add pineapple or grapes.
Chill.

title: colorful pasta salad
directions: Boil rotini until tender and drain.
Add other ingredients and mix dressing in thoroughly.
This recipe serves approximately 12 servings and is best after sitting in refrigerator overnight.

title: texas bar cake
directions: Bring the margarine, water and cocoa to a boil and cool.
Add dry ingredients:
flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Add the sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or well done.
Be sure cookie sheet is right size, no smaller.
Ice cake while hot.

title: squash quiche
directions: Slice squash and microwave for a few minutes.
Brown sausage and drain, then add cheese and butter.
Warm with sausage until cheese melts.
Remove from stove and add squash, paprika, pepper and sour cream.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Butter baking dish and put rice into dish.
Add water.
Add soup, onions, celery, margarine and thawed broccoli.
Spread top with cheese and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cube steaks in sauce
directions: In plastic bag, shake steaks in the gravy mix.
Brown quickly in butter.
Add remaining gravy from bag by adding some of the water to the bag and pour into the pan with the cube steaks.
Add rest of water to the pan.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
This is also good made with beef cubes and served over rice.

title: low-fat turkey chili
directions: Cook onion and turkey in a large pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for an hour.
Take out bay leaf.
Serve with Mexican Cornbread.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with chicken.
Pour mixed vegetables and juice over this.
Sprinkle chopped onion over this, then dot soup over all.
Mix flour, milk and butter; pour over other ingredients.
Do not stir.
Then pour 2 cups broth over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: candy bar pizza
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, brown and white sugars, oleo, egg and vanilla together; mix well.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips to this mixture. Place these ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
As soon as you take crust out of the oven, carefully spread 1/2 cup peanut butter and the balance of the chocolate chips on top.
It works well to take a teaspoon and place peanut butter in all areas, it spreads easier.
You may sprinkle your favorite candy bars on top.
The children will love this.

title: stuffed dates(quick and easy)
directions: Slice dates down the middle from tip to tip.
Stuff dates with a generous knifeful of walnut raisin cream cheese.
Arrange on platter and serve as an appetizer.
Watch how fast they disappear! Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: good old missouri country biscuits
directions: Mix dry
ingredients.
Add
shortening.
Mix shortening and dry ingredients.
Add
milk
and make a soft dough.
Place on a floured board
or table.
Knead lightly for a few seconds using small amounts of
flour on the board or table.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut
with a floured biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet
pan
or other greased pan.
Do not place biscuits too close together.
Bake
in hot oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 biscuits.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Remove husk from corn.
Wrap corn with wax paper.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
Butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: company seafood salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Mix all ingredients and chill for about 3 hours. Tastes like solid crab. Can use imitation crab.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine eggs, sweetened condensed milk and butter.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: green bean and tomato casserole
directions: Combine soup and green beans.
With ice cream scoop, mound leftover mashed potatoes on top.
Bake in Pyrex casserole dish until potatoes are lightly browned, about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°. A real favorite with our 5 kids and Gil!

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix together the crushed cookies and 1 stick melted butter; put mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Soften the ice cream; spread over cookie mixture in pan.
Refrigerate again.
Mix together the chocolate syrup, 1 stick butter and Eagle Brand milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cool, pour over ice cream.
Spread the Cool Whip over this.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and blend well.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Gradually mix in powdered sugar and salt until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until cool and firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Parboil cabbage and separate leaves.
Combine ground beef with rice, catsup, nuts and seasonings as desired, mixing well.
Spoon 2 tablespoons ground beef mixture onto each cabbage leaf, rolling to enclose filling.
Arrange cabbage rolls in a large soup pot. Top with lemon juice, garlic and tomatoes.
Place plate on top. Simmer for 35 to 45 minutes or until cooked through.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white until stiff. Blend in 1 cup brown sugar and vanilla flavoring. Dip pecans in mixture and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 200 degrees for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate caramel nut cake(turtle cake)
directions: 1. Wash and cut fresh strawberries.
(Depends on size of pan and how thick you want strawberries.
I used 3/4 of a half flat). Put in a bowl and add desired amount of sugar.
Set in refrigerator until almost ready to serve.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows in double boiler.
Add Hershey bars.
Remove and cool.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Use graham cracker crust.

title: easy wild rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Fluff the rice with a fork; add water if necessary, and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: pork chops & dressing
directions: Brown chops on both sides; place in casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs, onion, butter, poultry seasoning and 1/4 c.
water.
Mound on pork chops.
Pour soup mixed with 1/3 c.
water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: open-faced sandwiches
directions: On thinly sliced rye bread, spread thin layer of mayonnaise, then sweet onion, boiled or baked ham and Swiss cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly. Remove. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot.
Servings per person is usually 2 to 3 sandwiches each.

title: fudgie no-bakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by a teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.
Yield:
3 dozen small or 1 1/2 dozen large.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Sprinkle rice on
bottom
of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soups, celery and milk; pour
on
top
of rice.
Sprinkle with parsley, curry powder, poultry seasoning and
salt
as desired.
Lay pieces of chicken on top. Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil the last little while.
If baked 15 minutes longer, rice will be fluffier and chicken more tender.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in oblong or square pan.
Set out just before serving so it may be cut in squares.
You can also eat this without freezing.

title: cookie sheet apple pie
directions: In bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir until a dough forms.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll one-half to fit bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Arrange apples over crust.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cornflakes.
Sprinkle over apples.
Roll out the remaining dough. Place over apples.
Seal edges.
Cut slits in top.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix melted butter with cornstarch over low flame, heat.
Add grated cheese and milk.
Remove from
heat as soon as mixture starts to simmer.
Stir constantly.
Pour over cabbage.
Spoon together to mix well.
Add bread crumbs on top and let brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 slice ham and cheese on each breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight or prepare early in morning and refrigerate all day.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Can serve plain or with a white sauce on top.

title: cappuccino truffles
directions: Cook on high until almost melted, stirring until smooth. Freeze 1 hour or until firm.
With hands shape tablespoons into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts, cocoa powder or powdered sugar. Refrigerate.

title: low-fat cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and then add sugar.
Add salt and gradually add flour until stickiness is gone but not firm.
Let raise until double in size.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Roll out. Spread margarine over dough.
Generously spread brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut in 1-inch sections.
Let raise until double in size and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together yogurt, vinegar, lemon juice, curry powder and honey.
Refrigerate, covered, until serving time. Serve over mixed greens.

title: ham and vegetable linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: I use more onions and cheese.
Put half of tomatoes and onion slices in greased casserole.
Add salt, pepper and half of cheese. Repeat layers.
Dot with butter and put cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes the night before and soak in water; drain.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In 2-quart pan, melt butter, cheese and cream of celery soup.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over potatoes.
Cover with foil; leave 1 corner uncovered.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press onto bottom and side to form crust, sealing perforations.
tags: loose pack frozen hash brown potatoes

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugars, cinnamon, ginger, salt and pumpkin spices.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Crumble together and distribute over the apples in the pastry. Bake at 410° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together.
Divide into balls and roll into pie crusts. Can be frozen.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and saute onion, green pepper, celery and meat.
Pour off excess fat and place mixture in kettle with remaining ingredients.
Cook for 45 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese until soft and fluffy with a mixer.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 crusts.
Freeze until firm.
After frozen, cut into wedges.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Store in freezer.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream with shortening.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla. Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer pans at 325° for 10 minutes.
Increase heat to 350° and bake 10 more minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket(kids favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open Pillsbury crescent dough package and unroll dough.
You will note there are 8 triangles.
Take one triangle and cut into 3 separate pieces.
Take each piece and wrap around a hot dog.
Repeat with all triangles until you have all 24 hot dogs wrapped.
Place hot dogs on cookie sheet.
Place into oven and bake 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Let stand for 5 minutes for oats to absorb.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: morman bread
directions: Mix the oil, yeast and warm milk. Add to dry ingredients. Stir and mix well.
Put in a gallon jug or a large container. Do not tighten lid on jug for the first 4 hours.
It will rise to top of jug.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before rising.
When ready to use, pour out desired amount on a floured board.
Pat out and cut into rolls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: blueberry salad
directions: First layer:
Dissolve jello in water; add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Topping:
Beat cream cheese and sour cream until creamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and continue to beat until smooth.
Chopped nuts may be sprinkled on top.

title: best-ever brunswick stew
directions: Cook ham, chuck and hen together in a large stewing pot until tender.
Add the pepper pods.
Remove chicken from pot and bone. Cut into small pieces and return to pot.
Add catsup, tomatoes, paste, tomato soup, dash of Worcestershire and hot sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then frozen vegetables, butter and onion.
Cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add white beans and potatoes. Yields 8 quarts.

title: crispy caramel popcorn and nuts
directions: Stir together sugar, margarine, corn syrup, salt and vanilla in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and pour syrup mixture over popped corn and nuts in large shallow pan.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir mixture occasionally to prevent from sticking together while cooling.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: apple custard kuchen
directions: Cream oleo,
egg
yolks
and sugar together.
Add flour and mix.
Then	moisten
with
milk, enough to form a mix like pie crust.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mother-in-law egg special
directions: Mix well.
Let chill an hour.
You can also substitute eggs with Spam or fresh honey ham.

title: grandmother's devil's food cake
directions: Sift into mixture 1 cup flour.
Take 1 level teaspoon baking soda into 1 cup buttermilk; beat with a spoon until dissolved and milk rises.
Stir in and repeat with the flour and buttermilk-baking soda mixture.
Stir again.
Sift a third cup of flour in; stir well.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans and four cupcake sections (or use cupcake papers).
Should fill empty cupcake cups with water if you are using a cupcake pan with more than 4 sections.
Cook at 300° for 35 minutes, or 25 minutes for cupcakes.
Test with toothpick.

title: chicken & dressing casserole
directions: Brown chicken pieces in shortening.
Make dressing as follows: Melt margarine.
Saute celery and onion.
Add this to bread crumbs.
Add enough water to moisten as desired.
Place dressing in large baking dish.
Arrange chicken over dressing.
Make gravy from drippings where chicken was browned, blending with remaining chicken soup and add water to make 2 cups of gravy.
Pour over chicken and dressing.
Cover closely.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rolls
directions: Blend yeast and 1/4 cup water together.
Add sugar, Crisco, salt and egg.
Add 1 cup water and mix thoroughly.
Add flour and mix with a wooden spoon.
Add more flour, if needed, to make dough stiff.
Pat into a round ball and let rise in a covered bowl about 2 hours.
Knead down and shape into size rolls desired.
Let rise again 2 hours, covered.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chili
directions: Cut pork liver and pork chops in small pieces; cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper, plenty of onions and a little sage. Mash to make hash.
Serve with dry peas, stewed tomatoes and cracklin' bread.
Good winter meal.

title: pie shell for one 9-inch pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, shortening and water together until it is crumbly.
Knead or mix by hand until a ball is formed.
Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper, larger than a 9-inch pie pan. Remove top wax paper.
Place pie plate over crust and turn plate, crust and paper over.
Remove paper and shape into pan.
Pierce sides and bottom with fork.
Bake at 400° until light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water, stir in soft drink mix and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: stuffed scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cut tops from tomatoes; chop tops and set aside.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Reserve pulp.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot. Add onion and saute until tender.
Add chopped tomato tops, reserve pulp, salt and next 3 ingredients.
Stir well and remove from heat. Spoon stuffing mixture into tomato shells and place in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Add buttermilk to cottage cheese and blend on high speed, scraping sides often, until the mixture is smooth and creamy. Close in taste to real sour cream.
Use it on fresh fruits or baked potatoes or in any recipe that doesn't call for baking. This "sour cream" can't take the heat.
Yield: 1 cup = 175 calories.

title: do ahead frozen oven french toast
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Brush egg mixture over bread; pour it on both sides and let it soak up. Freeze a sheet of foil, uncovered, then package in Ziploc bags. When ready to eat, preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets heavily with Pam.
Brush both sides of frozen bread with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes, then increase to 400° to 425°.
Take pans out; turn bread.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: candied yams
directions: Put potatoes (washed and peeled) into large skillet.
Add butter and sugar.
Stirring mixture, cook on low heat, making sure sugar melts to form syrup.

title: banana cake 1945
directions: Put eggs, shortening and sugar together and stir until creamy. Add remaining ingredients, except bananas and nuts.
Stir well. Add bananas and nuts and stir.

title: ham quiche(this recipe makes 2 deep dish pie shells)
directions: In blender, mix eggs, 2 green onions and the cream; set aside. In unbaked shells, start with a layer of each cheese.
Add ham, mushrooms and chopped green onions.
Pour mixture from blender over this.
Bake in 425° oven until set, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: plain donuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add peanut butter, crumbs and powdered sugar.
Blend well and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together and spread on mixture. Cut into squares and refrigerate.

title: veal mozzarella
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt.
Dip cutlets in mixture and then into bread crumbs.
Brown in cooking oil.
Remove meat to shallow baking dish.
Saute onion and green pepper in skillet used for meat.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, spices and herbs; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over cutlets.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut cheese in slices and place over meat.
Return to oven until cheese melts (2 to 3 minutes).

title: italian pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Remove from pan; set aside.
Add rice to pan; stir until rice is coated with oil.
Add seasonings; stir.
Return pork chops to pan.
Cover with rice.
Add chicken broth; cover and cook until meat is tender and rice is cooked.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat first
ingredients in skillet.	Separately cook whole carrots until
tender; slice in rings over sauce.
After cools, add
onion	and
pepper.
Add
some
chopped
red sweet pepper for color,
if
you want.
Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.	The older it gets, the better.	This is good with vegetables and meats.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; pour 3/4 cup water over and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Put into greased loaf pan, bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix well and add margarine.
Mix well and sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake at 400° until the topping is nice and crunchy.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Mix sausage with raw rice.
Hollow out zucchini.
Place in baking dish and stuff mixture in hollow.
Pour 1/2 cup mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until sausage is done and zucchini tender.

title: mama's norwegian wheat rye bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in bowl.
Combine milk, egg and butter.
Stir into dry mixture until well combined.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Divide in half.
Lightly press each half into 1/2 inch thick rounds.
Transfer to buttered large baking sheet. Prick lightly with fork.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Transfer to rack until cool.

title: yummy desert
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°. CRUST; melt oleo in 9x13 pan, mix flour and 1/2 c. pecans and spread on bottom of pan. Bake 20-25 min and cool. SECOND Layer; beat till creamy powdered sugar and cream cheese, fold in 1 c. Kool Whip, and spread over cooled crust. THIRD Layer; Mix 3 c. milk to each pudding according to directions, spread on top of 2nd layer, add remaining Kool Whip and sprinkle nut on top.
Chill.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese until easy to stir (but not too much).
Add diced corned beef, diced green onions and picante sauce.
Mix well. Spread a layer of mixture over all of the tortilla shell.
Roll tightly and chill (usually overnight).
Use a sharp knife to slice into sections.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and shortening.
Cool to room temperature.
Add orange peel and juice and egg.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to date mixture and stir just until mixed.
Turn into 3 greased miniature loaf pans and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, or one 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake for 1 hour.
Cool, wrap and store overnight.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, pare and cube the eggplant.
Cook the cubes in water to cover.
Drain thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper; mash with potato masher.
Mash tomatoes with the onions.
Add to eggplant along with the cornbread crumbs.
Grease casserole dish with butter. Turn eggplant mixture into dish and pour in enough milk to cover. Top with grated cheese and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes with electric mixer until smooth; add cream cheese, sour cream and salt.
If mixture is too stiff, add milk. Place in casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: granny smith apple salad
directions: Gently mix dry pudding mix into whipped topping.
Fold in diced apples and candy.
Serve in lettuce cups, if desired. Serves 6.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Put the vanilla pudding in a bowl and mix with the pineapple juice. Stir until thick.
Fold in the fruit and add the Cool Whip last. Chill.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: holly's cole slaw
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; pour over the cabbage, carrots and onions.
(Lettuce can be substituted for cabbage.) Refrigerate until cold.

title: spice squares
directions: Put in a 10 1/2 x 16 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. While still warm, frost and cut into squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add jell-o. Cool to room temperature.
Place whole strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pool cooled mixture over strawberries and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: dropped tea cakes
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoons.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: merry cranberry margaritas
directions: Pour 1/4 cup cranberry juice into a shallow bowl.
Pour 3 tablespoons sugar onto a flat plate.
Dip the rims of 4 to 6 widemouthed glasses (6 to 8 ounce size, suitable for Margaritas) into juice, then into sugar.
Set the glasses aside.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes (until tender and golden), stirring once.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle garlic on chicken wings.
Put chicken in mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Remove chicken from mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fast fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle 1 box instant vanilla pudding over the fruit.
Stir. Add the marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Let stand at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices, mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool one minute on cookie sheet, then remove to a wire rack.

title: rigatoni with ham and peas
directions: It is essential that the sauce be made at the last moment.
It is best to start making the sauce when rigatoni goes into colander to drain.
Cook and drain rigatoni a shade more al dente than normal.
In a frying pan big enough to hold the sauce, melt butter over low to medium heat.
Add ham and salt and pepper to taste. Saute ham until warmed through.
Add cream and egg yolks, stirring constantly so cream and yolks do not separate.
Add Parmesan cheese and peas.
Mix together well.
Cook gently, stirring all the time until mixture becomes tepid.
Add sauce to rigatoni in large bowl. Mix well; serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour or overnight. For a 6-cup salad, 1 cup drained fruit cocktail or 1 cup chopped pecans may be added.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into 2 balls and chill.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together 1 minute the butter, sugar, cream or milk, cocoa and salt.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop from spoon to wax paper.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and drained pineapple and let stand 2 hours.
Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups hot water.
When partially cool, combine with cranberry mixture and allow to set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and pat vanilla wafer crumbs and butter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip eggs, powdered sugar, butter and vanilla for 15 minutes.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with crushed pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate and let set until ready to serve.

title: cottage pie
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic, salt and pepper to taste. Drain off excess fat.
Put meat mixture in square baking dish. Mix in cooked vegetables.
Layer sliced tomato on top.
Cover with mashed potatoes (may substitute instant potatoes).
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May make ahead of time, cover and refrigerate until used.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and form into crust.
Makes 2 pie shells. Freezes well.

title: texas gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour and sugar. Cut in butter. Set aside 1 cup of this mixture for topping. Add cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg and ginger to the remaining flour mixture. Stir in eggs and buttermilk. Do not use electric mixer. Pour the batter into a greased 9 x 12 pan. Sprinkle reserved topping over batter and bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: breaded venison chops
directions: Wipe off chops with a damp towel, making sure no bone dust from butchering remains.
Heat oil in large skillet at medium heat.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Dip chops into milk and egg mixture.
Mix together crumbs, garlic, basil and pepper.
Mix well.
Dip chops into crumb mixture.
Fry chops on medium until coating is medium brown.
When coating is medium brown chops are cooked, but still moist.
Serve.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Note:
Can use 1 (10 ounce) partially thawed strawberries; reduce white sugar to 2/3 cup.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichokes.
Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Delicious!
Bake and serve in the same dish.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: school-house yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar and hot water in a gallon jug.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk until water is lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir well.
Set aside and let it rise to the top of the jug.
Stir down then finish filling the jug with milk.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Freeze in packages of 2 dozen.
To serve, heat frozen balls in foil in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
In blender, blend eggs, salt, mustard and milk until fluffy.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 bread crumbs, 1/2 sausage, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 egg mixture, then layer remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes the next morning.

title: mom's casserole
directions: Fry onion with meat just to take the redness out of the meat. (It will finish cooking when entire casserole is baked.)
Boil noodles until almost done.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pepparkakor
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients.
Add next 3. Mix flour, soda and spices and add to first mixture.
Chill.
Cut into shapes and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauteed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season pork chops and place in shallow baking dish. Bake for 1 hour. Combine ingredients in bowl.
Pour over pork and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Take out and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate or grind cheeses, garlic and pecans.
Blend with hands and shape into small rolls.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in foil or Saran.
Chill.
Slice and top Ritz crackers.
Top with slice of stuffed olive to add color.

title: veal stew
directions: Cut up veal small. (I put it in the freezer for an hour or two, so it's easy to cut.)

title: hidden valley ranch chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Dip
chicken into melted butter. Dredge in bowl of	dressing
mix, cheese and cornflake crumbs. Bake, uncovered, in a well-greased
baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown (serves 4).

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in container.
Mix 2 teaspoons with 1 cup hot water.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add rice, onion soup and consomme.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Great with barbecue, chops or chicken.

title: sour cream soft cookies
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add sour cream alternately with flour mixture.
Add real lemon juice.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Add a raisin to center of cookie; sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix the first nine ingredients and blend well with mixer until smooth.
Fold in prunes, raisins and pecans separately.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake on center shelf for one hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together beef, egg, salt, pepper, onion and cornstarch. Shape into marble size balls.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Heat oil in skillet; brown meatballs.
Remove balls from skillet; wipe skillet clean of all drippings.
Combine pineapple juice, water and sauce mix in skillet, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add tidbits, green pepper and meatballs.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma k's chicken meshi
directions: Saute chicken in oil.
Add thinly sliced mushrooms, bamboo shoots and the rest of the ingredients except the rice.
Bring to a boil, making sure there is still sauce remaining.
Mix with rice in large bowl.

title: oil pie shell
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pie pan.
Combine milk with oil in measuring cup.
Whip with a fork until thick and creamy. Immediately pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix with fork until flour is completely dampened.
Press into shape in pie pan. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes per pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: white chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate.
Whip egg yolks in mixer until fluffy and pale yellow.
While eggs are beating, combine water and sugar in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 1/2 minutes. "Bloom" gelatin in 1 cup water and add to sugar-water mixture. Slowly add sugar mixture to egg yolks (on low speed).
Cut butter into small pieces and add to mixture one piece at a time.
Add Grand Marnier.
Add melted chocolate.
Pour into a stainless steel bowl.
Whip egg whites until they form soft peaks.
Fold into other ingredients.
Whip cream.
Fold into other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: horseradish mustard
directions: Mix all items in saucepan, except eggs and horseradish.
Let stand several hours.
Add eggs; stir with wire whip.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in horseradish.
Jar, cool, cover and refrigerate.
Keeps for several months.

title: amber's soup for the group
directions: In very large skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain well (if you are not well, you should not be cooking anyway).

In very, very large skillet, bring water to a boil and add all ingredients (I like to peel, clean and dice my veggies, but to each his or her own) except macaroni (if you did not read entire recipe first, don't try to fish the macaroni back out as it will not totally ruin the soup and would probably be a painful process to boot). Lower heat to simmer.
Let cook for 2 hours.
Add macaroni and cook for 20 more minutes.
This makes a tasty soup that is greatly enjoyed by myself, Ken, Barbie, Cindy, Jaz, Ari, Gaspar, Alladin, Ms. White, and all the rest of my gang of friends.
(Dolls, etc.)

title: elbow macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni first.
Drain and put into large bowl.
Add chopped, boiled eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix carrots, celery, bell pepper and onion in separate bowl thoroughly.
Then add to macaroni.
Top with grated cheese.

title: sweet and sour zucchini
directions: Wash and scrape zucchini lightly.
Cut into lengthwise slices, about 3/8-inch thick. Fry in oil about 3 minutes on each side or until slightly brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Remove zucchini from frying pan and place in a deep dish.
Mix throughly sugar and vinegar; add to remaining oil in frying pan.
Boil slowly for 2 minutes.
Pour over the zucchini.
Sprinkle with the chopped basil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: heath bar pudding
directions: Beat milk in pudding until thick.
Add softened ice cream. Crush graham crackers.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Put graham cracker mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put pudding on top of graham crackers.
On top of pudding, put Cool Whip.
Crush Heath candy bars; sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: toasted coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in thick skillet.
Add coconut and stir over low heat until golden brown.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter and cream cheese together. Add milk.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups toasted coconut.
Spread on top of cake layers.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on top.

title: spicy new england pot roast
directions: Rub flour, salt and pepper mixture into all meat surfaces. Brown meat on all sides in drippings.
Mix horseradish, cranberry sauce, spices and broth to meat.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Brown carrots and onion in drippings; drain. Add to meat.
Cover and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken and soups.
Mix 1 can milk or water with soup. Put oleo in and 1 1/4 cans of water.
Add to stuffing mix.
Mix and spoon on top of chicken casserole.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and syrup to a very soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Pour onto buttered platter.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.

title: apple pie with candied crust
directions: Arrange apples well in greased pie plate.
Mix together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut butter into mixture until like meal.
Pat on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Refrigerate.
Dip any cut up fruit.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients and place in casserole dish.

title: three pastry cobbler
directions: Mix 1 1/2 c. sugar with 1/3 c. plain flour. Mix berries with sugar-flour mixture. Place pastry in bottom of pan of desired size---either homemade or bought crust. Add layer of berries---dot with butter. Add another layer of pastry--- the berries---dot with butter. Place on the top crust and bake at 375° to 400° until brown and juice bubbles through top crust, (about 30 to 35 minutes).

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with crackers and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt oleo.
Add green pepper and onion.
Saute until tender. Add crawfish tails and saute.
Add soups.
Pour in tomato sauce and can of water.
Cook slowly.
Season with garlic salt.
Red pepper is optional.

title: easy onion soup
directions: Heat butter in a large pot.
Add sliced onions and fry slowly until golden brown, over low-medium heat.
Gradually add the beef and chicken broth.
Rinse each can with a little water and add to mixture.
Add the sherry and pepper to taste.
Cover and let simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Pour into ovenproof bowls. Place toasted French bread slices, butter side up.
Spread heavily with grated Parmesan cheese and dot with a dash of butter.
Place under broiler for 1 minute or until cheese is golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: secret surprise cookies
directions: Beat
butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add sifted
flour
and	nuts.
Beat
on
low
speed until well blended.
Remove
foil from kisses.
Heat oven to 375°.
Using 1 heaping
teaspoon dough shape with fork; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put one chocolate kiss on top of cookie.
After shaping on cookie
sheet bake 12 minutes or until are set but not
brown. Cool
on
wire rack;
sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: texmati rice pilaf
directions: Saute shallots in oil until slightly cooked. Add peppers and saute 2 or 3 minutes. Add rice. Toss to coat all grains.
Add garlic and tomatoes, then stock. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook 20 minutes or so. Fluff with fork and sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: corned beef oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
Tear corned beef into small pieces into egg mixture.
Stir in cheese and onion.

title: nancy's make ahead layered mushroom and eggs
directions: In pan stir soup and sherry or milk until hot and smooth. Set aside.
In bowl toss cheese, set aside.
Beat together eggs, soup mixture,
parsley, dill, and pepper.
Set aside.
In large fry pan melt butter; add mushrooms, onion, and cook until onion is limp. Add egg mixture; cook until eggs are softly set.
Spoon half egg mixture into 9 x 13 inch greased pan, spoon half mushroom mixture, and then sprinkle evenly with 1/2 of cheeses.
Repeat.
Top with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 30-35 minutes.
1 hour if refrigerated.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook pears until tender.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Fantastic over hot biscuits or as ice cream topping.

title: maryna's marinade with chicken
directions: Cook all ingredients together.
Cook chicken pieces in the marinade until tender, but not separating from the bones.
Remove and place on grill for a few minutes or eat as is.
The marinade can be served over rice, potatoes, noodles or with bread rolls.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until stiff.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream.
Let stand two hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: new england clam chowder(crock-pot)
directions: Fry bacon and onion in skillet.
In crock-pot combine the bacon and onion, clams, potatoes, water, bouillon and spices.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 4 to 5 hours.
About 1 hour before serving add half and half and evaporated milk.
Adjust heat to high and cook until heated through.
If necessary, thicken soup by mixing 2 tablespoons cornstarch with about a cup of the broth. Blend well, return to pot and cook until thickened.
Serve with hot crusty sourdough bread.

title: spinach dip or spread
directions: Squeeze spinach; get dry as possible.
Mix all ingredients. Serve with party rye bread or chips.

title: milky way icing
directions: Add sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat until it reaches soft ball stage.
Add and stir butter, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until chocolate chips are melted.
Remove from heat; stir until cool.
Spread on cake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend together with mixer (electric, hand or bowl stand). Pour mixture into pan over unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for approx. 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into pie shells. Refrigerate.
(Can be frozen.)

title: root beer cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix together in a 1 gallon glass jar with loose cover.
Stir several times the first day, then once a day for 2 weeks.

title: 1932 christmas fruit cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Beat 5 minutes. Add 2 cups flour, fruit juice and coffee.
Sift rest of flour, spices, soda and salt over currants, dates, raisins, cherries, citron, orange, lemon and pineapple.
Add floured mixture to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts and mix thoroughly.

title: easy crab soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Mix together all ingredients into crock-pot or large "Dutch oven" pan.
Heat on high (in crock-pot) for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
On stove top, heat until soup begins to boil, stirring occasionally.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Simmer tomatoes (peeled and cored), butter, salt and pepper until soft 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in milk and flour combined.
Return to heat and stir.
Cook until thick 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over baked potato, boiled potato, toast or anything else.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening in mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pineapple pie cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over wafers.
Mix well.
Put half of wafers in bottom of dish.
Cream the cream cheese and 1 stick margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Spread over wafers followed by pie filling and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle rest of wafers on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili con carne
directions: Combine beef and onions in a Dutch oven or large saucepan; brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients; stir to blend. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with crackers.
Makes six 1 1/3-cup servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter or margarine until soft and work in sugar until mixture is smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Slowly mix in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until the filling is firm and lightly browned on top.

title: seafood hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Spread into dish.
Add chili sauce.
Top with shrimp or crab (may use half of each); refrigerate.
Before serving, squeeze lemon juice on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: oven baked sweet potatoes
directions: Put sweet potatoes in casserole dish with water. Sprinkle with a generous amount of brown sugar and spoon the butter over the top. Bake at 350° until sweet potatoes are tender.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Put in fruit cocktail can and freeze solid.
When ready to serve, open other end of can and push out.
Slice off 1-inch slices of salad. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli with bouillon cube and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese and milk.
Melt.
Add broccoli.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: japanese-style hamburger
directions: Brown beef well in skillet, leaving meat in large chunks. Dissolve cornstarch and salt in water.
Add to skillet and bring to boil.
Stir in noodles; cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and bring to a full boil over medium heat, separating vegetables with a fork; stir until sauce cubes are blended.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce.
Makes 3 servings.

title: pear relish
directions: Put first 4 ingredients through the coarse blade of the food chopper.
Mix the remaining ingredients; add the first 4 and bring to a boil, cooking slowly, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned.
Drain and get your dough on a 12-inch pizza pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spoon sausage over crust; sprinkle with potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over pizza.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Place grape leaves on tray or waxed paper and set aside. Mix all ingredients, except grape leaves and lemon juice, together and blend well.

Take 1 grape leaf at a time and place 1 tablespoon of filling across leaf. Fold sides in and roll away from you. Arrange stuffed leaves in pot and alternate with direction with each row. Sprinkle extra salt on tops. Cover with plate. Cover with water to cover top of the plate. Cook, covered, on medium heat for about 40 minutes or until rice is done.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with parsley.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream Crisco until soft, then gradually add sugar and beat until light.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in warm water, then add the flour which has been sifted with the salt.
Stir in orange, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: apple nut cheese biscuits
directions: In a bowl, stir together sugar, nuts and cinnamon; set aside. Stir together biscuit mix, Cheddar cheese and chopped apple.
Make a well in the center of the mixture; add water all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Form into a ball.
Flatten dough out on floured surface.
Divide into 18 small pieces; shape each into a ball.
Roll into melted margarine, then in sugar mixture. Arrange in a greased 9-inch round baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vermicelli pie
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions; drain.
Stir butter and Parmesan cheese into hot vermicelli.
Add eggs, stirring well.
Spoon into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Use a spoon to shape noodles into a pie shell.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 9 minutes or until set.
Combine beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread Ricotta cheese evenly over pie shell.
Top with meat sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; sprinkle with Mozzarella and top with pepperoni.
Bake, uncovered, about 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peach crisp("a very good desert.")
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13 glass dish. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Set on rack to cool.

title: jayne's swiss baked chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In your baking dish, place the chicken, breast side up, then put 1 teaspoon vinegar on each breast.
Put cheese slices to cover breast; put the undiluted soup over the cheese.
Then put the stuffing mix on top and pour over the one stick of melted butter.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 45 minutes, depending on the thickness of the breast.
Delicious served with brown or mixed rice and salad.
Looks and tastes real fancy!

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, dressing and soup mix.
Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sauce on chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and uncover chicken and let brown 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oven pot roast with vegetables
directions: Wipe off roast with damp paper towel.
In hot butter in 6-quart Dutch oven, brown roast well, turning on all sides with wooden spoons, over medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Remove roast; set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Add chopped onion and garlic to drippings in Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes, or until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour until smooth.
Add vinegar, honey and broth; stir to mix well.
Tie bay leaves, parsley and black pepper in cheesecloth bag.
Add to Dutch oven. Bring to boil, covered.
Roast 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Meanwhile, place carrots and onions in 3-quart casserole dish.
Add water to measure 1/2 inch.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Bake, covered, in oven along with pot roast, 1 1/2 hours, until fork-tender.
Remove cheesecloth bag from oven and discard. Remove pot roast, carrots and onions to heated platter.
Serve with sauce from Dutch oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, vanilla, sugar, milk and salt.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour peaches over dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit cooler
directions: Add raspberry Kool-Aid to sugar and pineapple juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Add remaining fruit juices.
Chill.
Serve over ice. Makes 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, Grape-Nuts, sage, onion, salt and pepper together; make into 24 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in grease.
When meatballs are browned, push to side of pan.
Mix flour into fat; add water and simmer 15 minutes in covered frypan.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients, cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake cake mix according to package directions, using 2 layer cake pans.
Cool cake layers well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut bread in chunks and pieces and put in a buttered casserole dish or buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix thoroughly and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir after first hour.
Serve warm with ice cream and caramel sauce.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan (4 quart capacity) over medium heat without stirring.
Let cook until mixture turns from clear to golden yellow.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir. Mixture will foam, while it is foaming add popcorn to it.
Nuts may be added, if desired.
Place in a greased pan to cool and with buttered hands form into balls.

title: maraschino quencher
directions: Mix fruit juices and ginger ale.
Add honey; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Add ice cream (I use French vanilla).
Stir to blend. Top with sliced and whole cherries.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix cheeses and nuts.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Stir in nuts or your choice and chocolate chips. In a separate bowl, beat eggs and vanilla together, then stir in cookie dough. Mix until blended (if dough is too dry, add 1 or 2 tablespoons of water). Shape by teaspoonfuls into round, flat ball. Bake at 375° for 9 minutes. Let cool. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Cook together dates, sugar and water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add nuts.
Cool.

title: old fashion date loaf
directions: Mix together sugar and milk in saucepan.
Cook until a soft ball forms when dropped into a cup of water.
Remove from heat. Add dates.
Mix until dates are melted into sugar.
Add chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Pour out on a long strip of cold wet cloth. Fold over and over with hands.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut in slices.

title: laila's crabalicious dip
directions: Unwrap cream cheese, place on plate, dump crab meat and sauce on top. Eat with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, powder, soda, salt and cinnamon in bowl. Mix until well blended, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add oil while mixing.
Add carrots and eggs one at a time, mixing well after each.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop all vegetables well. Cover with cold water and let stand 5 minutes. Drain and add the sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes. Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Place in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix until just blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: sweet and tangy sausage
directions: Place sausage links in a baking pan and bake until browned. Pierce skin during cooking to release fat and drain.
(Smoked sausage may be used-boil it 10-15 minutes and drain.)

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice sweet potatoes. Sprinkle with sugar (plenty).
Fry in oil; bacon fat is better. Let brown lightly on each side.

title: pig-pickin' cake
directions: Combine cake mix and mandarin oranges.
Substitute pineapple juice for water required on box instructions.
Prepare according to package instructions. While cake is cooling, combine drained pineapple and Cool Whip. Add sugar to desired sweetness.
When cake is cool, spread Cool Whip mixture on layers.
Cake must be refrigerated.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer casserole dish with cabbage, salt and pepper.
Brown meat and onion; layer over cabbage.
Mix soup and ketchup; pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: mother's garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into a ball. Decorate with olives and/or pimento.

title: oven fried chicken wings
directions: In 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch roasting pan in a 425° oven, melt butter.
Remove pan from oven.
On wax paper, mix bread crumbs, flour, salt, rosemary and pepper.
Pour buttermilk into small bowl.
Dip 1 chicken wing at a time first in buttermilk, then in crumb mixture to coat.
Place chicken wings in melted butter in roasting pan, turning to coat evenly.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad in artichoke cups
directions: Simmer garlic and wine in small saucepan 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cut bottoms of artichokes flat and remove outer leaves. Cut 1-inch from tops; snip tips from remaining leaves and rub ends with lemon.
Add artichokes, wine-garlic mixture and 1 tablespoon oil to 2 inches boiling chicken broth in large saucepan.
Cover; simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until leaves pull easily from base; drain.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until creamy. Sprinkle cheese and other topping on top.
Chill. Use chips and dip.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot mix.
Just before mixing these, beat the mix on high speed just a little.
Bake in very hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes; turn back to 350° and bake until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift and mix flour, baking powder and baking soda. Combine with creamed mixture.
Spread half of mixture in pan. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, chocolate chips and nuts. Sprinkle half of this mix over batter in pan.
Spread remaining batter in pan, then remaining topping mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bars
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add beaten eggs and beat. Add baking powder to 1 cup flour and add to mixture. Add milk and flavoring and then add remaining flour. Work until it will roll out. Cut and bake at 350° until done.

title: cabbage and pork and bean soup
directions: Fill large pot halfway with water.
Add meat, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
Slice cabbage and add.
Add beans and vinegar. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 to 4 hours.

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix together well.
Make into logs.
Wrap in plastic wrap and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: e-z salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in bowl; add sour cream, nuts, jello and pineapple with juice.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into 8 inch sq. dish. Melt marshmallow in milk in double boiler; stir until smooth. Chill to thicken.
Combine softened cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Whip in marshmallow mixture; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Top with cherries.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: luki's doggie treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix until you have a stiff dough.
Roll out about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick on a board or pastry cloth.
Use a dull knife and cut out bone shaped biscuits.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake about 12 minutes.
Let your pup or dog enjoy!

title: judy's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour mixture into melted butter in casserole dish (9 x 9-inch).
Pour fruit on top. Heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: heavenly four layer pumpkin torte
directions: In medium
bowl, combine margarine and flour and cut in until mixture
resembles	coarse	meal.
Stir
in nuts.
Press into bottom of
x
13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 325°. Cool.

title: homemade bread (italian)
directions: Use 1 cup of warm water to dissolve the yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar; mix well.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: apple pecan squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Mixture will be stiff and sticky.
Mix well.
Add apples and pecans.
Mix well again.
Spread in large oblong pan, 13 x 15 x 2-inches.
Place in a 350° oven and bake 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes more.
During the last 10 minutes of cooking, prepare the sauce.

title: charlotte's beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
