Add pimento and sour cream.
Pour into greased casserole dish; top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Then add pineapple and nuts.
Then add Cool Whip.
Stir well and pour into two graham cracker pie crusts and refrigerate until set.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: After mixing steak, onion, garlic powder and butter, cook until brown.
Add all 4 cans of soup and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add cooked noodles (drained) or rice.

title: quick tomato spice cake(origin: unknown)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake following directions on the package. If desired, fold in 1 cup chopped walnuts before baking. Frost with favorite white frosting.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Put all in blender and blend.
Pour half into bowl and refrigerate until set.
(Let other half set in blender.)
When set spread with a layer of sour cream and pour rest of jello on top and refrigerate until set.
You can use any flavor jello you want.

title: fastnachts
directions: Mix well. Roll about 1/4 inch thick cut pieces 2 x 3 inch. Cut 2 slits in center fry in deep fat.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and fruit juices and mix until smooth.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serves 10.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pie filling with milk. Blend in 1/2 Cool Whip and condensed milk. Pour filling over arranged wafers and bananas. Garnish top with the other half of Cool Whip. Chill.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Place 6 bread slices (cut in half) on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup Cheddar cheese, broccoli, ham and remaining 6 bread slices.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in milk and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Great for breakfast or supper.

title: herbed pork chops(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix the rosemary, sage, garlic, salt and pepper.
Rub the chops with the mixture.
Place the chops in a large greased skillet.
Add the water.
Cover.
Simmer until all the water has evaporated, about forty-five minutes.
Remove the cover and brown the chops in their own fat.
Add the wine and cook about one minute, turning the chops occasionally.
The wine should be almost evaporated before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients just by stirring.
No mixer necessary. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit topped cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese and sugar until creamy.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Spoon cherry pie filling onto top of pie.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip if desired.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops and set to the side.
Cook rice until almost done.
Slice tomato, green pepper and onion; set this aside also.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Mix together your favorite meat loaf and put
in
a 9 x 13-inch pan (should be fairly thin).
Bake at
350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
While hot, spread soup over
meat loaf, then spread on green beans.
Next add Tater Tots
in
rows.
(Sometimes
I use
a biscuit recipe and drop unbaked
biscuits
on
top
in rows.) Put back in oven and bake at 350° until all ingredients are hot or biscuits are done, approximately
25 to 30 minutes. You
can keep a meat loaf ready in the
x
13-inch
pan
in freezer.

title: rice pudding
directions: Spray a 2-quart glass dish with Pam.
Preheat oven at 350°. Combine all ingredients and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large pan and bring to boil. Boil 2 minutes, then remove from stove eye and stir in the peanut butter and oats. Mix well, then drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: garden new potatoes
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp. Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.

Add potatoes and onions to bacon drippings. Cook over high heat until lightly browned. Drain excess bacon drippings. Add chicken broth. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add mushrooms and cook, uncovered, over high heat, stirring constantly, until liquid evaporates.
Stir in bacon, salt, pepper and parsley.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes with all ingredients except milk and butter. Cook slowly; when potatoes are done, mash mixture slightly.
Add milk and butter.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix margarine, milk, egg, vanilla and molasses together; stir into flour mixture.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at room temperature.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter; put in casserole with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine all ingredients except dressing and stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 quart casserole or Corning Ware dish.
Top with dressing cubes which have been mixed according to package directions.
Bake at 350° covered with foil for 45 minutes, then 15 minutes uncovered.

title: best ever orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let egg whites come to room temperature, in large bowl.
Measure flour and sift with salt. Beat egg whites at medium speed until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1 1/2 cups sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: red and white bean salad
directions: Discard seeds from tomatoes; dice tomatoes.
Peel cucumber but leave on some green.
Discard seeds from cucumber; dice.
In medium bowl combine all ingredients.
Makes 4 servings.

title: the "last bananas" brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together butter and sugar until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In saucepan, bring to boil, stirring. Cook for 2 minutes. Makes 2 cups of sauce.

title: sweet and sour beans(excellent)
directions: Place beans in a 3-quart casserole.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Fry until nearly crisp.
Remove bacon.
Drain on paper towel.
Discard half of the drippings.
To remaining drippings in skillet, add vinegar, onions, brown sugar, mustard, salt and garlic powder.
Cook 20 minutes or until onions are tender, stirring often.
Add mixture and bacon to casserole.
Stir to mix.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mystery cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Melt oleo or butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour the flour mixture on top of it. Add cherries, peaches or strawberries.
Pour sugar over top.
DO NOT STIR. Bake at 400° until brown.
Cobbler like crust forms around front. Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: summertime casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Saute onions and mushrooms in oleo. Add ham, chicken and seasonings; heat.
Combine sour cream and cottage cheese; add to spaghetti.
Add ham and chicken mixture; toss lightly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Add

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together the sugar, cinnamon and pecans in a bowl.
Pull the bread dough apart into small pieces.
Dip in melted margarine and roll in other mixture.
Put the pieces into a round cake pan. Drizzle any remaining margarine on top.
Cover with a towel and let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it springs back.

title: rosie's chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and set aside.
Dice onions and chop up lettuce. Combine ingredients.
Fry about 1/4 package of wontons in oil; slightly brown.
Toast seeds on baking sheet until golden brown. Add wontons and seeds to salad.
Add dressing just before serving salad.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix margarine and flour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat mixture down evenly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with can of blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Cut steak into cubes and brown in oil in a skillet over medium heat. Drain pimentos and mushrooms. Add to browned steak.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover skillet and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chuckeroni
directions: Cook meat in skillet until browned.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cook on low heat until vegetables are soft. Add macaroni and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a large pan.
Heat to dissolve.
Do not boil.
Add peanut butter and Special K.
Mix well and put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: heavenly fruit hash
directions: Combine fruit, sugar and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream and keep chilled until served.

title: quick chili
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2 1/2-quart bowl; add onion and garlic powder.
Microwave at High power for 3 to 4 minutes or until all pinkness is gone; drain well.
Sprinkle seasoning over beef; stir to combine.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Cover loosely and microwave at High power for 12 to 15 minutes, stirring 3 or 4 times during cooking.
Garnish each serving as desired with shredded cheese, sliced ripe olives and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries.
Blend until smooth and fold in berries.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325° or until done.

title: apricot dip
directions: Combine apricots and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers, such as Wheat Thins.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Mix in strawberries.
Cool in refrigerator while preparing other steps.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add pretzels.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Meanwhile, mix together and spread on pretzels, pour on jello mixture of cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: edward's italian cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Separate 5 eggs and add yolks.
Beat in, one at a time.
Add buttermilk, sifted flour, soda, vanilla, coconut and chopped pecans.
Whip egg whites and fold into mixture.
Cook in 3 layers or large loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes or Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add well beaten eggs.
Add as many raisins or currants as you wish (1 cup).
Alternate dry ingredients with the milk and vanilla.
Roll, cut out and bake on griddle.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir dry potatoes, sugar, butter and hot water together.
Stir in cold water and baking mix.
Mix until smooth. Knead on floured board until smooth.
Roll dough and cut into biscuits.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: christmas crunchers
directions: Line baking sheets with waxed paper, coat with cooking spray. In large mixing bowl, combine pretzels, noodles and peanuts; set aside. In pot over medium heat, melt marshmallows with butter; cook, stirring until smooth. Pour over reserved pretzel mixture; stir until well coated. Coat hands with cooking spray, shape mixture into 1 1/2 in. mounds, place on baking sheets. Using fork drizzle stacks with melted candy melts.

title: pumpkin roll cake
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer 5 minutes; gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold flour, powder and spices into pumpkin.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool.
Unroll.
Spread with filling made of combined cream cheese, 1 1/3 cups powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla blended until smooth.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate ice-cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees and adjust the shelves to the upper third of your oven.
Lightly butter large baking sheets.
In a large bowl, stir in flour, baking powder
and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine the butter, sugars, oil and corn syrup. Mix in the egg and vanilla extract until blended, then gradually add the flour mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips and nut, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add eggs
to
pumpkin
and
beat well.	Add salt, milk, sugar and
flavorings.
Add a teaspoon of pumpkin pie spice if desired. Pour
into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese and spam
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed except using 3/4 cup milk.
Add peas and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Arrange Spam squares on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into ball.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: patty's chicken pie
directions: Rinse and drain frozen vegetables. Saute onions in butter. Add broth and milk and heat. Add flour and salt and pepper to make a gravy. Stir in chicken and vegetables. Pour mixture into pie shell and cover with top pastry and crimp edges. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Add pineapple, then remaining dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Drop with teaspoon. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix ingredients; divide into 5 (1-gallon) jars; seal and store in refrigerator.
Several hours before serving, fill a heart shaped mold with some of the punch and freeze to float in punch bowl.
Yields 125 cups.

title: squash dressing
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix all ingredients except margarine and pour into oblong greased baking dish.
Pour margarine over top. Bake 25 minutes at 425° or until brown.
Serves 12.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Add cheese and broccoli; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, flour and salt. Place berries in pastry shell. Spread sour cream mixture over berries. Combine bread crumbs, 2 Tablespoons sugar and margarine and sprinkle on top. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: white icing(for decorating or frosting)
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
Add milk and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the pork chops.
Dip pork chops in sauce and lay in baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce over chops.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until chops are tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco mix. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients together, adding Doritos and Catalina dressing last.

title: peachy keen nog
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at medium speed until smooth.
Serve.

title: browned-flour soup from basel(basler mehlsuppe)
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons of butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in the flour; cook together over medium heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon until smooth and the color of chocolate (takes about 7 to 10 minutes).
Do not let the mixture scorch.
Remove from heat; gradually add the hot liquid, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add onion, bay leaf and salt to taste.
Simmer over lowest possible heat, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
Remove onion and bay leaf.
Serve with grated Swiss cheese on the side.

title: spaghetti
directions: Add salt to hamburger and brown in large saucepan.
After hamburger is lightly browned, push to one side of pan.
In opposite side of pan, place finely diced onion and garlic in hamburger grease and cook until tender; stir.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well and place over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 4 hours.

title: blush apple pie
directions: Combine ingredients and let set while preparing 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine together and cook over low about 1 hour.
Pack hot into sterilized jars and seal.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Crush cornflakes to equal 1/2 cup. Combine ground beef, cereal, cheese, garlic salt, pepper and egg. Shape one tablespoon of mixture into 1-1/4 inch balls. Place on ungreased 15 x 10 x 2 inch baking pan and bake 15 to 17 minutes, or until no longer pink. Turn meatballs halfway through cooking. Drain on paper towels. Serve with sauce (optional). Makes about 30. Can be frozen for later use.

title: knew dream pie
directions: Beat together pudding, gelatin and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish or pan with whole graham crackers on bottom.
Pour on half of pudding mixture.
Put another layer of graham crackers.
Add rest of pudding and top with another layer of graham crackers.
After pudding sets, frost with chocolate fudge icing of your choice.
Refrigerate.

title: no bake sweet potato pie
directions: In saucepan, mix gelatine and spices; blend in eggs, beaten with milk.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Heat over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Blend in potatoes.
Pour mixture into prepared crust. Chill until firm.
May be served with whipped cream and chopped nuts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Before you start mixing let cream cheese set out until room temperature.
Mix in a bowl, then put it in the graham cracker crust.
This batter has enough to make 2 cheese cakes.
Let set in the refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Add fruit topping if desired.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Cooking Time: 50 minutes.

title: florentine artichoke dip
directions: Drain spinach to remove excess water. Combine spinach, artichoke hearts and next 5 ingredients in a bowl, stirring well. Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish. Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over spinach mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes. Serve with crackers, bagel chips or breadsticks. Yields 4 cups.

title: french cream peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and egg until creamy.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar; add creamed mixture, blending well.
Chill slightly for easier handling.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin ice cream bars
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place into graham cracker crust.
Cover with foil or wrap.
Freeze until firm. Portion and top with whip cream and serve.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar and coffee together.
Add boiling water.
Stir to dissolve and cool.
When cool, add vodka and vanilla; stir.
Pour into dark bottle; let stand for 2 weeks, shaking bottle 2 times a day.

title: tofu enchiladas(vegan recipe)
directions: Freeze, thaw, squeeze dry and tear or chop into bite size pieces 1 1/2 pounds tofu.
Have ready 12 corn or flour tortillas. Prepare either chili gravy or tomato sauce (see following recipes).

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut off ends of peppers; clean out seeds and wash.
Set aside. Cut cheese into 10 small squares; stuff cheese into peppers.
Set aside.
Mix milk and eggs together; mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, meal, salt and pepper in bowl.
Dip each stuffed pepper in egg mixture and in flour mixture.
Deep fry in oil for 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat egg, sugar and oil.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well.
Add carrots, vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Stir until all ingredients are all mixed.
Put in bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix last 2 ingredients.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trece's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts 45 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces. Boil noodles; drain and put in cold water.
Mix noodles, chicken meat and all else together.
Bake at 350° in 3-quart casserole for 1 hour.

title: big boys strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem berries.
Drain.
Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add Jell-O and let cool 15 minutes.
Lay berries in pie shell and pour glaze over top.

title: sweet potato cookie bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add butter and mix until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: vegetable soup whimpies
directions: Saute onions and green peppers until tender; then add meat. Cook meat until it turns brown.
Drain.
Then add vegetable soup and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: ranch pasta primavera
directions: Cook rotelle noodles; drain.
Stir in olive oil, Ranch dressing mix and vegetables.
Heat and serve.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together and scoop onto greased cookie sheet with ice cream scoop.
Flatten slightly with heel of hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon graham crackers
directions: Place crackers on cookie sheet, lightly greased.
Combine the margarine, sugars and nuts in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes or until frothy.
Let cool until frothy goes down.
Spoon on the crackers, 1 teaspoon on each cracker.
Place in oven at 300°.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Unroll	French	bread
and
cut
into
even	pieces. Sprinkle with pepper.
In a frying pan, crumble up sausage and add peppers and onion until cooked;
drain fat.
Mix in 3/4 of the beaten
eggs.
Pour
half of sausage mixture in middle of each square of bread.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and roll up. Brush sides
of
bread to seal edges.
Baste top with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cookies and cream fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt white chocolate squares, Eagle Brand and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in cookies. Spread evenly into foil lined 8 in. square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Crush pretzels with rolling pin.
Mix with margarine and sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Beat together Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over cheese layer.
Refrigerate, uncovered, until jelled, then cover.

title: roast chicken
directions: Cook gizzard, heart and meat for about 1/2 hour.
Chop fine and use broth of same to mix dressing.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage and drain.
Mix meat and ingredients.
Put in dish.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Place bacon, onion, green and red peppers and celery in large skillet.
Let fry
to
minutes
or
until bacon is crisp. Add shrimp.
Cook
for 10 minutes.	Add cooked rice to shrimp and other
ingredients,
sprinkle about 1/4 cup La Choy soy sauce over rice, stir until brown, season to taste, lower heat for 5 minutes.
Serve
hot.
This recipe can be used with chicken or pork.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cook on top of stove until almost done.
Get medium or large casserole dish.
Grate cheese and put a layer of cheese on the bottom of dish.
Put a layer of potatoes, then cheese.
Repeat until dish is full.
Add milk, butter, salt, pepper, seasoning salt and top with more cheese. Cook in the oven with cover on for 3/4 of the way to keep moist. Cook on 375° for 1 hour.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft, not mushy!
Cool in refrigerator. Slice cooled potatoes in thick slices and place in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add mushrooms and heat thoroughly. Combine onion, mushrooms, rice and consomme in 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, combine zucchini, biscuit mix, parsley, onion, salt, Parmesan cheese, eggs, oregano, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Mix well. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread mixture in baking pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool slightly and cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add cheese; beat with mixer.
Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add 1/3 of onions to potato mixture. Salt to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender and add soup.

title: creamy chicken with angel's hair
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in oil in large frying pan.
Remove from pan.
Cook and stir vegetables and garlic in same pan 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in sauce.
Add chicken; cover.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: grandma's dumplings
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy saucepan over medium heat, stir soup, water and butter until smooth. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Heat griddle or skillet to medium heat (340°).
Top each of 4 slices of bread with 1/4 of the corned beef, sauerkraut, dressing and cheese.
Cover with remaining bread slices.
Spread margarine on outside of each sandwich.
Place sandwiches on griddle; grill on each side until golden brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let zucchini, salt and onions set overnight.
Rinse off and squeeze excess water out.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let everything cook for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Spoon into hot jars and let seal.
Makes 7 pints.

title: quick casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion, then drain.
Cook rice; add tomato soup. Mix contents together.
Place in an ungreased casserole pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet cook sausage until browned.
Drain off excess fat. Separate crescent dough into triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points towards the center.
Press over the bottom and up the sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Put egg yolks in a 1 cup measuring cup; finish filling to top with condensed milk.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.

title: scandinavian fruit soup
directions: If bananas or strawberries are not available, the fruit soup containing only the orange juice, pineapple and Mandarin oranges is also excellent.
You can add your own choice of fruits.

title: strawberry cocktail
directions: Mash berries well; add sugar and lemon juice and let stand 3 hours.
Add water; strain and stir until dissolved.
Let stand on ice one hour.
Serve in tall narrow glasses, reserving 3 or 4 whole berries for each glass.
Raspberries, currants or other fruit may be used.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until real stiff.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before using a spatula to lift macaroons from cookie sheet.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut up vegetables and set aside; combine in small bowl the vinegar, sugar, salt, cayenne and Accent and set aside also. Brown garlic in hot oil; stir-fry pork in garlic until well done. Add vegetables and stir-fry for about 1 minute.
Add sauce and stir, then cover and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch paste and cook until sauce thickens.
Do not overcook.
Serve with rice.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add egg, warmed milk, sugar and salt.
Mix well, then add flour and shortening.
Use enough flour to make stiff dough.
Place in large bowl and let rise double in bulk.
Work down and form into rolls.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 400°.

title: banana split smoothie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in container of an electric mixer. Top with cover.
Process until smooth.
Add yogurt, process until blended.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 cups.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: bean-corn casserole
directions: Drain and mix beans and corn.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix together celery soup, sour cream, onion and cheese.
Spread over vegetables.
Work this mixture into vegetables a little with a fork.
Crush the Ritz crackers and mix with melted oleo.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: daddy's special
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper to taste and chilies in bowl. Pour into heated butter in skillet.
Cook until partially set, stirring constantly.
Add picante sauce.
Cook to desired consistency, stirring constantly.
Spoon into serving dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Yields 5 servings.

title: maple nut fudge
directions: Boil syrup, cream of tartar and butter to 233°.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Add walnuts and salt.
Pour into greased shallow pan.
Cool and cut.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line cookie sheet with the crescent rolls.
Bake 7-8 minutes according to directions.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread on baked crescents.
Chop 1/4-1/2 cups broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and green peppers.
Put on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and pat down with wax paper.
Chill and slice.

title: pretzel hugs n kisses
directions: *May need more than one bag of Kisses depending on how many to be made.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Save chicken broth.
Add the chopped potatoes, onion, carrots and celery to the chicken broth.
Add the large can of tomato juice.
Add the chicken.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
when the vegetables are almost done, add the 2 cans of corn and a pinch of sugar.
This soup is really good!

title: baklava(an authentic greek recipe)
directions: To make syrup, combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Strain and allow to cool.

title: holiday salad
directions: Combine water and cranberry sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Place pecan halves on top of Jell-O.
Put into refrigerator to set.
Serves 16.

title: never fail cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients and put in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread fruit and juice on top of mixture in pan.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring to boil water and salt. Add rice (Minute). Chop and saute celery and onion.
Put Cheez Whiz, cream of chicken soup and milk in with rice.
Mix broccoli in and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: garden vegetable dip
directions: Mince one cup carrots.
Mince one cup each broccoli and cauliflower.
Combine carrots, broccoli and cauliflower, onion, cream cheese and seasonings in food processor.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: eclaire pie
directions: Combine pudding, Cool Whip, milk and powdered sugar together. In a square cake pan, make layer of graham crackers, then a layer of pudding, then a layer of graham crackers, etc.
The last layer should be graham crackers.
Then ice with chocolate frosting. Chill for couple of hours, then serve.

title: low calorie chicken casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and bake in casserole 30 to 45 minutes.

title: beeferole
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Add salt, sugar, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic powder and pepper and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package.
Soften cream cheese; add sour cream.
Mix well and add onions.

title: fudge bars
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan with foil.
Place butter in pan and melt.
Combine next 4 ingredients, spread over butter.
Blend cream cheese and egg.
Gradually add frosting mix, stirring well. Spread over mixture in pan.
Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices and arrange over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes, or until cookies are light brown.
Invert immediately in cookie sheet.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly before cutting. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine everything and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Heat oven to 450°.
Place pie in oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until set.
Place pie on lower rack of oven and place a rack above pie with a cookie sheet on the rack over pie.

title: whole wheat bread or buns
directions: Mix yeast, 1/4 cup water and 1 tablespoon brown sugar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased bowl.
Let raise until double.
Punch down and make loaves or buns.
Put in pans.
Let raise again.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: jiffy chocolate bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in medium mixing bowl.
Combine oil, egg, milk, melted chocolate and vanilla in small mixing bowl, stirring well.
Make a well in the center of flour mixture.
Add oil mixture and mix until smooth.
Stir in pecans.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine rolled oats and boiling water; let stand 10 minutes. Cream together butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Mix with oatmeal mixture.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla, baking soda and salt. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough or just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through. (Use a handle of a spoon on cutting board to prevent knife from cutting all the way through.)
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: *Hint:
For buttermilk, substitute 1/2 cup milk plus 1 teaspoon vinegar.

title: cranberry crimson mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually whip in salad dressing until smooth.
Stir in cranberry orange sauce and applesauce.
Pour into 5-cup mold, which has been sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: river rat ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream.
Divide and spread into pie crusts.
Place in freezer until frozen.
Melt marshmallows and semi-sweet chocolate chips in double boiler.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Mix well.
When mixture cools to room temperature, spread over pies. Top with chopped pecans.
Cover and freeze.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: norwegian apple cake
directions: Heat butter and milk to boil, then cool until warm. Beat eggs and sugar well; add to warmed milk and butter. Add flour and baking powder to mixture. Pour mixture into a 9-inch round spring pan and arrange apples on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour batter in 2 loaf pans (greased) and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: Break the
cake
into
small
pieces in the bottom of a glass bowl.
Make
up the jello using the syrup from the fruit cocktail. Add
the
fruit to the cake and pour the jello over the top;
mix slightly just to moisten the cake and refrigerate.
Make
up
the pudding and add on top of the jello layer. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Some Suggestions:
1 can mandarin oranges, 1 can sliced pineapple, 3 bananas, 3 kiwi fruit, fresh strawberries and grapes.

title: roast pecans
directions: Preheat oven 300°.
Stir pecans into melted butter. Toast for 30 min or until done. Toss with salt.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms and drain.
Mix together clams, butter, bread crumbs, Parmesan, onion, Worcestershire, garlic salt and Tabasco.
Stuff ingredients into mushroom caps and top each one with Cheddar cheese.
Place mushrooms on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: frozen biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl, then cut in the Crisco with 2 knives.
Then add 3/4 to 1 cup buttermilk and mix with a fork lightly.
Knead about 1/2 minute.
Pat or roll out. Cut with biscuit cutter (but don't twist cutter).
Freeze on a cookie sheet (encased in a plastic bag).
Store in a Ziploc bag in freezer.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Remove as many as needed.
Don't thaw.
Cook until slightly brown.

title: pesto
directions: Blend pine nuts and garlic in a blender.
Add chopped basil leaves and olive oil.
Blend.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Arrange blueberries in a lightly oiled 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine with a fork or pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over fruit.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Let boil until it reaches soft ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oleo.
Beat until right consistency.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Nuts and raisins can be added, if desired.
Very good.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add slightly beaten egg white.
Add cream and milk slowly, blending well.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange walnut fudge
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan, combine sugar, water and orange juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and comes to a boil.
Continue cooking until 234° on a candy thermometer, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces and orange peel.
Fold in walnuts.
Spread candy in a foil lined 9 x 13 inch pan.
Chill until set.
Cut into small pieces. Store in refrigerator.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes without skins. While hot, mash with oleo, peanut butter and vanilla. Add nuts and enough powdered sugar to form balls. Ready to eat.

title: ethel fortenberry's egg custard
directions: Mix milk, sugar and oleo in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Pour hot mixture into eggs slowly while beating.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.
Outside will be set, inside quivery. May test for doneness by inserting tip of sliver knife in center and it will come out clean.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Brown beef and seasonings together; drain.
In separate pan, combine soups, milk and green chilies.
Simmer over low heat.
In casserole dish, layer chips on bottom, then beef, then soup mixture and then cheese.
Repeat layers another time.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with ham and then cover with Swiss cheese.
Place pats of butter on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: plantation beans(country style green beans)
directions: Fry bacon in pot; when done, remove bacon and then saute onion in bacon fat.
Add beans (with ends snipped); add water and cook over super low heat.
When almost done, add salt (optional because of salt in bacon).
Also add pepper and vinegar.
When beans are tender, add in bacon pieces, crumbled.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add liquids, cranberries and nuts.
Use a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Combine seasonings in small bowl; mix and set aside.
Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add the onions, celery, bell peppers, green onions, garlic, Tabasco, Worcestershire and pre-mixed seasonings.
Saute until mixture starts sticking excessively (about 7 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Stir in milk and catsup.
Continue cooking for about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool to room temperature.
Place ground beef in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add the eggs, bread crumbs and cooked mixture, removing the bay leaves.
Mix by hand until thoroughly combined.
In the center of the pan, shape mixture into a loaf.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes, then raise the heat to 400° and continue cooking until done, about 35 minutes longer.

title: stuffing for poultry
directions: This stuffing may be stuffed into poultry or baked in a separate casserole for 1 hour along with the roasting poultry in a skillet.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni (drain).
Melt butter and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat a large frying pan over medium heat.
Spread half the butter on one side of each tortilla.
Put one tortilla, butter side down in the hot pan.

Sprinkle the cheeses evenly onto the center of the tortilla in the pan -- but not all the way to edge. Put the tomato, onion, bacon and jalapeno over the cheese and cover with the other tortilla butter side up (like a grilled cheese sandwich).
When the bottom side is browned, about 45-90 seconds, flip the quesadilla and grill the other side.
Remove the quesadilla from the pan.

title: fruit swirl squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except fruit, and mix to combine.
In a buttered (greased) 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1/2 the batter, then spread fruit and spread remaining batter on top.
Cut through a few times only with a butter knife to swirl (fruit).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken supreme veronique
directions: Split breasts into halves; bone halves.
In skillet, place boned breasts, skin side up.
Add wine, water, onion or shallots and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat for 15 minutes, or until fork-tender.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine
oats
and boiling water; let stand at least 20 minutes.
Cream
together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add, mixing
thoroughly,
eggs,	vanilla and the oat mixture.
Sift together
flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir flour
mixture
into
the
egg mixture.
Beat about 2 minutes, then turn into a greased cake pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gourmet on the go delicious spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Simmer until smooth and thick, about 35 minutes.
Serve over cooked pasta. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together in large pan.
Roll in balls and bake at 350°.

title: heavenly fruit cocktail
directions: Blend pudding and milk with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Fold in fruit; reserve 1/2 of the orange for garnish. Serve in a pretty bowl with orange slices garnishing the top. (You cannot taste the buttermilk.)

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and keep in closed container. Refrigerate (will keep many months).
Serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour and cocoa.
Add all other ingredients. Mix together well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan (sprayed with Pam). Bake in glass dish at 325° about 20 to 25 minutes.
Other dish, bake at 350°.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine milks, tapioca and sugar and stir.
Cover and vent.
Microwave on High 3 minutes until slightly thickened.
Uncover and microwave on High for 4 minutes until thick.
Using a wire whisk, in separate bowl, lightly whisk egg yolk.
Gradually add to milk mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Microwave on Medium, uncovered, for 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. With electric mixer on high, beat egg white until stiff.
Gently stir egg mixture into egg white.
Put into 4 custard cups.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Serves 4.
Contains 107 calories, 2 gm fat and 85 mg sodium.

title: oatmeal jelly cookies
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in oats.
Into a bowl put soft shortening and vanilla. Mix in slowly the brown sugar.
Beat in vigorously the egg.
Stir in about 1/3 of the flour mixture.
When smooth, stir in about 1/2 of the milk.
Repeat until all flour and milk are used.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet, leaving 2-inch space between each.
With back of teaspoon, press hollow in each.
Put into hollows 1/2 teaspoon jelly.
Bake 12 minutes or until brown. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Follow directions on cake box.
When mixed, pour in a sheet baking pan (bread pan), then take strawberries that have been thawed and dip juice and berries around on top of cake mix.
Bake until done.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine sauce ingredients in small saucepan; heat gently and use for basting or for hamburgers.

title: apple delicious
directions: Flatten biscuits with glass.
Wrap 1 biscuit around each apple half.
Place in baking dish.
Bring sugar, margarine, water and cinnamon to boil in saucepan.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour around apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: chocolate covered peanut balls
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and stir in
sugar,
graham
cracker crumbs and flavoring.
Shape into balls
and
place
on cookie sheet.
Insert toothpick and chill an hour or two.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; add eggs, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Add crushed potato chips and stir until blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork dipped into a cup of hot water.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 to 8 dozen.

title: bean pot
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until onions are clear. In baking dish, mix well ingredients, beans, catsup, sugar, mustard and pepper.
Add onion mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese.
Put potatoes and ham or pork roll in casserole and pour cheese sauce over and stir to cover potatoes and meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix browned meat and onions and set aside.
Mix first eight ingredients together, then pour 1/3 of cornbread mixture in pan. Place meat and cover with rest of mix.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven in approximately 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: paula's famous night shift jello
directions: Make jello according to package directions for 4 small packages or 2 large packages.
Add no water for 5th package, just mix with others.
The decreased amount of water makes the flavor stronger and supports the peaches.
Add 2 cans drained peaches and put in fridge in a 2 to 3-quart container until firm.

title: merry sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine. Add eggs and flavorings. Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Chill two to three hours. Divide dough in half. Roll out on lightly floured board. Cut with cookie cutter. May sprinkle with sugar or frost, when cooled. Bake at 375° for
7 to 8 minutes or until light gold. Makes 5 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: cushaw cake
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white.
Add brown sugar, then pecans.
Spoon into pan in small balls.
Bake at 275° for 35 minutes.

title: dressed eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 10 minutes, then cool in water.
Take shell off egg and cut in half.
Take yellow of eggs and place in bowl with sugar and salt.
Add enough Miracle Whip to make into the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Spoon into egg whites; sprinkle with paprika.
Chill for 30 minutes before serving. Cover when chilling.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a small bowl. Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract in a large mixing bowl until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels. Drop by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are set. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes; remove to wire recks to cool completely.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil.
Add crackers.
Stir.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; sprinkle with butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover with crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crisp crusted chicken casserole
directions: Beat egg and milk in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix potatoes, garlic and cheese.
Roll chicken pieces first in egg mix and then roll in potato mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan and roll coated chicken pieces in it.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: three soup dish
directions: Mix soups and butter.
Put rice in baking dish and cover with broth.
Let set for 1 hour.
Pour half of soup mix over rice. Place chicken parts on top; cover with rest of soup mix.
Bake, covered, for 2 1/2 hours at 350°; uncovered last 1/2 hour.
Cover with cheese and return to oven to finish baking.

title: homemade banana layer cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add banana, buttermilk, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on racks.
Serves 12. Frost with Boiled Frosting recipe.

title: funnel cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking powder and salt).
Mix eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients; stir until smooth.
Place 1/2 cup batter into funnel with 1/2-inch opening. Place finger over spout.
Pour batter from funnel over hot vegetable oil 1/2-inch deep.
Swirl batter in shape of coil. Brown on both sides.
Drain; dust with powdered sugar.

title: babs' scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Cook and stir in milk slowly. Add salt and cayenne.
Cook sauce until smooth and boiling.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add pepper.
Grease baking dish.
Alternate layers of potatoes and sauce in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, water, yolks and lemon juice until thickened, stirring constantly. Then add butter, lemon extract and vinegar.

title: halloween pumpkin squares with cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream sugar and oil, add eggs and pumpkin.
Add dry spices, then flour and mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet with small lip on edge.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick; should come out clean.
Let cool completely.

title: congo bars
directions: Sift flour and add baking powder, soda and salt.
Sift again. Melt shortening in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar. Cool.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips and mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Combine mayo, horseradish, chili sauce and lemon juice and refrigerate.

title: mexican cobbler
directions: Mix sauce and bring to a boil in a saucepan.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla extract. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add together.
Mash bananas.
Add sour cream, bananas and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar over top. Slice and serve warm or cooled.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add evaporated milk.
Cool until consistency of whipped cream.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice; beat with beater.

title: double crust mayonnaise pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix well. Sprinkle with water.
Mix well.
Press firmly into ball with hands.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Blend nuts and fruit into cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and store in either freezer or refrigerator.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, brown sugar and 1 1/2 cups milk in blender.
Blend until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans and vanilla into blender. Chop pecans for a few seconds.
Add the mixture from the blender into the freezer can with the Eagle Brand and Milnot.
Fill the can with the rest of your milk.
Freeze as normal.

title: quick baked alaska
directions: Turn oven temperature to 475°.
Spread dessert shells with jam or jelly.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake dessert shells with jam or jelly for 5 minutes.
Place a scoop of ice cream in center; top with whipped cream and serve.
Serves 4.

title: russian chicken
directions: Combine ingredients for marinade.
Spread layer in pan.
Place chicken on top and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (covered).

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts together and press into baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: summer peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix peaches, 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon in large bowl.
Cream butter and remaining sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients just until blended.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Arrange peaches on top attractively.
Bake about 50 minutes or until done. Cool in pan; dust with sugar.

title: sweet-n-sour sauce with pork chicken or shrimp
directions: Combine juice from pineapple with cornstarch, water, brown sugar, ginger, soy sauce and vinegar in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Set aside.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes, brown meat with garlic and onoin in 3 teaspoon oil. Stir in vegetables and stir-fry.
Pour sauce over meat and vegetables and serve over rice.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Put in rhubarb. Sprinkle with jello, then sugar.
Sprinkle dry cake mix next. Dot with oleo and pour water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.
Mmmm good!

title: eggplant with crusty coating
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip into lightly beaten eggs.
Drain and dip into coating made with the breadcrumbs, Italian seasoning and Parmesan cheese, mixed.
Oil the bottom of a shallow baking pan.
Place eggplant in it.
Spray the top with cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn once.

title: white cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Set aside.
Mix together first 4 dry ingredients.
Add oil, egg yolks, water, vanilla and orange extract.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Use two ungreased 9-inch pans; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or use 10-inch tube pan and bake 70 to 80 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients in large bowl and beat until very thick.
This will make 1 quart.
Put in jars and put in cool place. Refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and oil together.
Pour over combined vegetables. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add other ingredients and congeal.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup, milk, green pepper, pimento, pepper and half of the cheese crackers.
Pour into shallow 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with remaining crackers and crumbs. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach and artichoke party dip
directions: Combine light sour cream and dip mix in medium bowl.
Stir in artichokes, spinach and pimientos.
Cut slice off top of round loaf of bread.
Hollow out center of bread leaving 1-inch shell. Reserve bread pieces for dipping.
Spoon dip into bread shell. Serve warm or cold.
To serve warm, bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cover loaf with foil if browning quickly. Serve with bread cubes and/or assorted fresh vegetables.
Serves about 12.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat at high speed of an electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Stir in orange extract, dates, pecans and 1 tablespoon orange rind.
Pour cake batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake layers in pans 10 minutes.
Remove layers from pans; let cool completely.

title: fruited cranberry mold
directions: In a large saucepan, dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cool water; add cherry
gelatin
and
2 cups hot water and cook on medium heat until all gelatin is dissolved and mixture is transparent. Add 1
cup
cold water; put gelatin mixture in refrigerator to chill.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Bring water to boil; add Jell-O and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve sugar.
Add Kool-Aid, apples, bananas, strawberries, fruit cocktail, kiwi and grapes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Add mashed potatoes to cheese mixture and beat until smooth. Transfer to 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles from box.
Meanwhile, fry hamburger, onion and pepper until brown.
Drain.
Add sauce from dinner and spaghetti sauce.
Stir together.
Spoon small amount of sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer noodles over sauce.
Sprinkle cheese over noodles.
Spoon sauce over cheese.
Continue layering in pan, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great with garlic bread.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple (do not drain) and pistachio pudding. Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix; add marshmallows and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone; cut in chunks.
Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add juice.
May add chopped and leftover celery to chicken while cooking.

title: bambinos
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread crackers with catsup.
Top with pepperoni slice and some cheese.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until cheese melts, 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 dozen canapes.

title: cheese dip in bread(my favorite)
directions: Cut top off bread and save.
Hollow out round bread and toast the bread chunks.
Mix together cheese, mayonnaise and picante sauce.
Pour cheese and mayonnaise mixture into bread and put top on.
Wrap in foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add applesauce which has had soda added to it.
Mix cocoa, raisins, nuts and spices together.
Add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in a 250° oven.

title: hamburger veg dish
directions: Layer in casserole in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy applesauce muffins
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl. In separate bowl, combine applesauce and baking soda; add to creamed mixture with dry ingredients (batter will be stiff). Store batter in covered container in fridge until ready to bake. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full; bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 muffins.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and approximately 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on box (leave water in rice, do not drain).
Melt cheese and tomatoes in microwave.
Combine all ingredients, add a few crumbled chips to mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle crumbled nacho chips to the top of the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dirty sock chili
directions: Brown meat in oil (small amount of oil) then add the rest of the ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all, marinate meat at least 6 hours or ideally overnight. Turn to stir several times while marinating.

title: pennsylvania dutch shoo-fly pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Dissolve 1 teaspoon soda in hot water.
Mix with molasses. Stir until well mixed and set aside.
Then mix and sift together flour and soda and add sugar and shortening.
Work with fingertips to make crumbs.
Pour soda water and molasses mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Empty peaches into shallow baking dish.
Add tapioca and let stand ten minutes; add sugar, salt and spice.
Mix well, dot top with butter.
Roll biscuit dough to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Prick and arrange over top of peach mixture.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes or until well-browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: minestrone in minutes
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Cook uncovered over medium-high heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix
ingredients together;
shape into ball and roll in crushed walnuts.

title: vanilla melts(a cookie)
directions: In
bowl
stir	together first 3 ingredients.
In large bowl with
mixer
at
medium speed, beat butter until smooth. Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Will be very stiff.
Refrigerate
hour.
Shape
into 1-inch balls. Place about
1/2-inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Flatten with lightly floured fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until edges
are	lightly
browned.
Makes
dozen.
Very short and delicious.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered corn flakes.
Bake 1/2 hour or more at 350°.

title: wings and things
directions: In a baking pan, pour 1/2 the amount of oil to coat the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 the package of gravy mix, 1/2 amount
of soy
sauce and 1/2 of all seasonings into the pan. Lay chicken wings, sausage and potatoes in the pan.
Coat with remaining
oil, soy
sauce and seasonings.
Cover and bake at 350°
for
hour. Uncover
and
cook
for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add 2 cups water.
Stir to dissolve. Add remaining water.
Add pineapple and stir.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Other flavors of Kool-Aid may be used to change the color of the punch.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Place butter or other shortening in saucepan and melt.
Mix in brown sugar (add 1 tablespoon water if vegetable shortening is used).
Stir in beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and chopped nuts together; add to mixture.
Mix well and spread in greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash but do not peel zucchini.
Cut into slices.
Cut bacon into pieces and thinly slice onions and separate into rings.
Cook bacon in skillet over medium heat; add onions and cook for 5 minutes more.
In a large casserole, place layers of zucchini slices; sprinkle with salt, pepper, dried basil and catsup.
Cover with layer of onions and bacon and repeat until casserole is filled.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy baked corn
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Pour into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch
baking
pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: baklava
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and walnuts. Melt butter in small pot.
Lay several sheets of phyllo dough in 9 x 13-inch pan (or your largest pan).
Spread some of the walnut mixture on the dough.
Drizzle butter on walnuts.
Continue alternating dough, walnuts, butter.
Top layer should be dough. Cut into squares or diamonds.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: super squash casserole
directions: Place squash, onion, sugar (optional) and salt in a 4-quart saucepan.
Cook for 20 minutes; drain well and mash.
Mix eggs, 1/4 pound grated cheese, milk, melted margarine, flour and seasoned salt (to taste).
Add to squash mixture; stir well. Spoon into casserole dish; top with 1/4 pound grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: heavenly pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar, flour, corn syrup, melted margarine and vanilla and mix well.
Place pecans in pie shell and pour egg-sugar mixture in pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes longer.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve when cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa and salt; then sift together.
In a separate bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add coloring and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk (about 1/3 of each, each time) and mix well after each addition.
In a small bowl, mix vinegar and soda and stir in last.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: gob stoppers
directions: Place chocolate in a large glass bowl.
Heat on High or full power for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Add peanut butter and rice cereal.
Stir until cereal is well coated.
Fold in marshmallows.
Spoon into mini-cups and chill at least 10 minutes. Serves:
About 2 dozen pieces.
Preparation time:
15 minutes. Chilling time:
10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cover shredded zucchini and set aside. Beat together oil, sugar and eggs. Add cinnamon. Combine dry ingredients. Thoroughly combine egg mixture with flour mixture. Add vanilla. Lastly, add zucchini, including all liquid in the bowl and mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or cake pan or muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Additional nuts and chips may be sprinkled on top before baking.
When cool, cut in bars.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Blend celery soup with 1/2 soup can water.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture.
Combine with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, minced onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into balls, about 1-inch round.

title: stir-fry chicken with snow peas
directions: Take ends off peas.
Cut the chicken into bite-size morsels, leaving some skin on.
Get rid of the bones or use to make stock. Place the chicken morsels into a bowl with 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon of wine.
Place the mushrooms into a bowl of boiling water and let stand for 15 to 30 minutes, then drain and squeeze off excess water.
Blend tamari, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons wine.
Blend and stir in 1 tablespoon cornstarch, stir to blend and set aside.
Heat 2 cups of oil in a wok.
When the oil is hot, add the chicken, stir for 3 to 4 minutes to cook, then remove the chicken.
To the hot oil in the wok, add the mushrooms and snow peas and cook for 30 seconds.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Cook beef, onions and pepper for a short time.
Add mushroom soup, tomato soup, 1 can water and chopped pimento.
Make two layers.
First a layer of noodles, then beef mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan butter pan biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 9-inch square baking pan, melt butter in oven, 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl except milk.
Stir in milk just until moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth.
Roll dough into rectangle.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Dip strips in melted butter. Place in same pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, then resift with spices, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Add soup, water, oil and eggs, then chopped nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese rice pork
directions: Cook rice in oil until brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon cube and soy sauce.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and 1/4 cup more water, if necessary.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: cheese olives
directions: Cream butter and cheese
until soft.
Add egg and water and beat well.	Sift
flour,
cayenne
and
paprika
together. Beat well.
Chill for
10 minutes.
Roll mixture around olives and freeze.
Remove from freezer
and
bake in a 400° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
This
same
recipe
can be used for cheese straws, omitting the olives and using a cookie gun.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix together instant vanilla pudding and milk.
Mix like you would to make pudding.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Layer graham crackers in the bottom of an oblong pan. Cover graham crackers with pudding mixture.
Put another layer of crackers and cover again with pudding mixture.
Put another layer of crackers and frosting.
Refrigerate.
Make up 24 hours ahead of time.

title: our yum yum salad
directions: Note:
If canned blueberries are used drain well.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cook half the venison, half the onion and half the mushrooms in 1 tablespoon hot margarine in a skillet until onion is soft and meat is some tender; set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, venison, mushroom and onion.
Return all meat mixture to skillet. Cook a while longer to make sure venison gets tender, then stir in soup, Miracle Whip, parsley flakes and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream.
Gently heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: aburage
directions: Slice aburage thinly and pour boiling water over it.
Drain well, then squeeze aburage until almost dry.
Mix remaining ingredients and add aburage.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, 7-Up and salt until clear. Add Jell-O. Cool. Fold in strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: corey's devil dogs
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by full teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: three week wine
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Mix in juice.
Put the balloon on top of the jug.
Balloon will blow up.
When balloon deflates, wine is ready, about 3 weeks.

title: mr. dell's potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 c. butter or oleo, and pour into 9x12 pan.
Add 1/2 pkg. hash browns.
In separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream, milk, onions and pour half of mixture over hash browns.
Sprinkle 1 c. grated cheese on top.
Add remaining hash browns.
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top, and cover with crushed crackers.
Pour 2 Tbsp. melted butter or oleo on top.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Spray foil generously with vegetable cooking spray.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch strips.
Toss potatoes in jelly-roll pan with oil, garlic, salt and pepper to coat well.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, tossing once or twice until potatoes are crisp and golden. Calories 195, fat 2 g per serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix in a bowl the flour, powdered sugar and margarine with mixer until all crumbly.
Then press into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or less.
Let cool.

title: oatmeal carrot cookies(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan with vegetable oil.
Cover raisins in a small bowl with boiling water.
Soak 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: frittata(similar to quiche)
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking pan.

title: rabbit stew with dumplings
directions: Place rabbit in 8-quart pot.
Add water.
Cover pot and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove 1/2 cup of broth to a glass jar and place in freezer.
Remove rabbit. Cool.
Strip meat from bones and return meat to pot.
Bring to boil; lower heat and let simmer to pot.
Bring to boil; lower heat and let simmer for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove liquid from freezer.
Add 1/2 cup flour to jar.
Cover.
Shake well.
Add to pot.
Return to boil.
Add dumpling mix.
Return to simmer and cook for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook an additional 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Preparation Time: 2 hours.

title: zesty baked chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, pepper and salt.
Combine margarine with garlic; dip chicken in the margarine.
Roll each piece in bread crumbs mixture.
Place chicken pieces in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs mixture.
Bake until tender, about 50 minutes, at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 2 layers.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Top each layer with 1 package of strawberries.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and 1 package of strawberries for icing.
Freeze or refrigerate.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Turn into shallow casserole. Top generously with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute mushrooms in a little butter, then remove and saute onions. Mix together soup, sour cream, mushrooms, onions, olives and chili powder. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Spray bottom of casserole dish with Pam. Spoon enough sauce to cover bottom of dish. Sprinkle 2 tbsp. chicken into tortilla and add 2 tsp. of sauce and a little cheese. Roll up. Continue until all are used. Pour remaining sauce over all the enchiladas. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with electric mixer.
When they are frothy, add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time and cream of tarter.
Beat until stiff.
Stiff is when you turn off mixer and lift out of mixture the peaks stand up straight; if they do droop, beat a little longer.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine cranberries, water, orange peel, cinnamon sticks and cloves in large saucepan; cook until cranberries are soft. Strain.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and sugar to strained mixture.
Heat over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Serve.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onions and bell pepper in large skillet till meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, then salt, chili powder, and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes, or until thick.
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Turn into greased 9-inch x 9-inch x 2-inch baking dish.

title: crab spinach dip
directions: Saute crab, spinach, green onions and garlic salt in butter. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Serve with crackers.

title: calico beans salad
directions: Drain 1/2 juice from kidney and lima beans.
Fry and drain bacon.
Remove bacon and fry hamburger in same pan.
Remove hamburger and saute pepper and onion in pan.
Place all ingredients in baking dish or crock-pot and cook until bubbly. Serve hot or cold.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, and water in a 3 qt. saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in butter. Stir frequently after mixture reaches 230° on candy thermometer. Add nuts when temperature reaches 280°.
Stir constantly until temperature reaches hard crack stage (305°).
Remove from heat; quickly stir in baking soda, mixing thoroughly.
Pour onto well-buttered cookie sheets. Spread as thin as possible with spoon.
Let cool.
Loosen from cookie sheets and break into pieces. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: chicken dish
directions: Spray casserole dish with cooking spray.
Line bottom of casserole dish with dried beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Place each breast on top of dried beef.
Combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour soup and sour cream mixture over chicken and dried beef.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1-1/2 hours.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Add scrambled eggs and chopped Spam (grease must be sponged off first).
Add bacon, onions, mushrooms and soy sauce to taste.
Heat completely and serve.

title: red bell pepper soup
directions: Saute vegetables until softened.
Add broth and cream.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Puree in blender.
Simmer soup 15 minutes or more.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: deluxe turkey salad
