directions: Sprinkle turkey breast chunks with lemon juice and salt. Chill several hours. Add rest of ingredients and toss lightly. May be served on lettuce leaves.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Put other ingredients, except butter, in a bowl.
Pour melted butter into mixture.
Mix with a fork.
Spoon mixture over apples, covering completely.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until apples are soft.
Serve in small dishes topped with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: company chicken
directions: Trim chicken.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter.
Add soup and 1 can water.
Chop onion and add last. Cover and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: red, white and green salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Combine vegetables. Add mayonnaise mixture and toss.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Line serving bowl with lettuce leaves and fill with salad just before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Heat soup with chopped onion and butter.
Stir into cornbread and add sage, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 9-inch square dish and heat in microwave.

title: orange banana bread
directions: Beat batter until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in banana and orange rind.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture alternately with orange juice, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix at low speed.
Stir in pecans and raisins. Spoon batter into two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pans on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: kielbasa dinner
directions: Combine sausage and vegetables in Dutch oven.
Add water, bay leaf, garlic and caraway seed.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf and garlic.
Arrange sausage and vegetables on platter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cinnamon tea rolls
directions: Unroll dough onto lightly floured wax paper.
Press perforations to seal.
Brush with melted margarine.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Roll up jellyroll fashion, starting at long side.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in lightly greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and drizzle with Orange Glaze.

title: lentil chili(you'll never miss the meat in this super-delicious low-fat
directions: Heat oil in 5-quart kettle over medium heat; add onion, red and green bell peppers, coriander and cinnamon; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft (about 5 minutes).
Stir in sweet potatoes and cook, stirring often, for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, lemon juice, saffron and garbanzos.
Season to taste with salt.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 more minutes.

title: cold pizza
directions: In shallow pan, press out crescent rolls to make crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, mayo and dill together.
Layer on top of baked crust.
Top with pieces of carrots, broccoli, tomatoes and onions.
Chill.
Cut into 1 or 2-inch squares and serve.

title: stephanie's pickled peaches
directions: Peel peaches.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook until mixture boils well.
Add fruit and cook until tender.
Put peaches in sterilized jars.
Fill with hot syrup.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and break into pieces.
Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Add bacon and beans to beef and onion mixture. Add brown sugar, catsup and vinegar and mix well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Slice, cook and drain carrots.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of water.
Add this to sugar and vinegar mix.
Cook until clear and thick.
Fry bacon; drain and crush.
Pour sauce over carrots and add bacon.

title: date nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Lastly, add dates, nuts and vanilla.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut milk, lard and salt into the flour until well mixed.
Form into a ball and chill.
Makes two 9-inch crusts.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, milk and Cool Whip in a bowl by hand until mixed.
Pour in crust.
Place in freezer until firm.
Place in refrigerator.
Sprinkle top with graham crackers for looks.

title: chocolate pinwheel
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
To one part, add melted chocolate.
Roll out chocolate dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper to form a rectangle about 15 x 16 inches.
Roll out plain dough the same way.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Put 3/4 of the mixture in a baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Combine the next 4 ingredients in a saucepan, and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour custard over peanut butter mixture.
Top with meringue made with leftover egg whites.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mix over meringue.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put oats in boiling water.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, flour, shortening, eggs, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well on lowest speed of mixer.
Add vanilla, nuts, cinnamon and oats.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 14 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done.
Top with following icing.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups flour in large bowl with salt and Kool-Aid. Add oil and boiling water; mix well and slowly add flour.
As mixture cools, your child can help knead dough on floured board. Stop adding flour when mixture no longer sticks.
Store in Ziploc bag in refrigerator.

title: roman round steak
directions: Sprinkle the round steak with tenderizer and let stand one hour.
Dredge in flour and brown in oil.
Remove meat; put in roasting pan.
Blend in hot drippings and ingredients listed.
Pour over meat and bake uncovered at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Melt slices of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Stir in all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Drain and cut chestnuts in half.
Cut bacon slab in thirds while still chilled.
Wrap each chestnut up in strip of bacon, toothpick and stand in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off grease thoroughly.

title: creamy dreamy cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs and sugar; stir in butter thoroughly.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate; bake 10 minutes.
Remove from
oven and cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, blend together all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
This pie freezes well.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, or in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add 1 can kidney beans, drained.
Chop lettuce, onion, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Add to hamburger mixture with 1 bag crushed Doritos.
Eat immediately.

title: potato cakes
directions: Beat eggs and mix thoroughly into the mashed potatoes along with the onion and flour. Form into biscuit-size patties about 1 inch thick. Spread butter on each side of patty and fry at medium temperature until golden brown on each side.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar, Rice Krispies, milk and egg and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and dates; mix.
Cool before rolling in coconut.
Keep in cool place.

title: jogger in a jug
directions: Mix up and keep in refrigerator.
Drink 2 ounces daily.
Good for arthritis.

title: grand central oyster pan roast(a new york recipe, for 1 serving)
directions: Combine oysters with their liquor (juices), clam juice, 1 tablespoon of the butter, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce and celery salt in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Whisk vigorously (without hurting oysters) for 1 minute until the oysters' petticoats begin to ruffle (edges start to curl).
Add cream.
Stir over boiling water for 1 minute more.
Place toast in wide soup bowl.
Pour pan roast over toast.
Dot with remaining tablespoon of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Grease 24 muffin cups (paper liners can be used also).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat sugar, sweet potatoes and butter until smooth. Add eggs and blend well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Add alternately with milk to sweet potato mixture, stirring just to blend.
Do not overmix.
Fold in raisins and nuts, spoon into muffin cups and sprinkle each with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: quick waffles
directions: Beat eggs, milk and shortening in small bowl at medium speed until blended, about 30 seconds.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to first mixture.
Beat and blend about 1 minute.
Preheat waffle iron at high.
Using about 7/8 cup of batter per waffle, bake 5 to 6 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses at room temperature until well blended.
Add rest of ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into ball and roll into nuts.

title: no-bake fudge cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in sauce pan and cook until it boils. Boil 1-3 min. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and instant oats.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together instant pudding, Dream Whip and cold milk.
Beat until it forms soft peaks.
Spread over cooled cake.
Layer the drained, crushed pineapple over the entire cake.
Next, spread the large container of whipped topping over the pineapple.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve the sauce over chicken with rice or noodles.

title: texas glop
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce, corn, salt and chili powder.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Put in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: tex-mex cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces. Cook about 10 minutes or until tender, but crisp.
Put in greased casserole. Saute onion and green pepper in melted margarine; add sugar.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: aunt gladys' blueberry pie
directions: Place 3 cups raw blueberries in baked shell.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil; when cool, pour over berries in the shell. Chill.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots until tender, drain.
In large bowl combine potatoes, carrots, ham, green pepper and onion.
Stir together.
Combine celery soup and milk.
Stir until blended.
Add soup and cheese to vegetable mixture.
Pour in oiled baking dish. Mix together crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger in skillet. Drain. In crock-pot, combine sausage and hamburger along with remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally until cheese is completely melted. Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: barbecued pork sandwiches
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine meat, onions, chili powder, salt, water, ketchup and vinegar.
Cover and simmer for 4 hours or until meat falls apart easily.
Skim off fat with a slotted spoon; remove meat, shred into small pieces and return to liquid and heat through.
Serve on buns.
Leftover pork roast can be used, can be frozen.

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix well.
Press and flatten to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Combine milk and eggs, then add to cheese mixture.
Mix just until moistened. Spoon into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Remove from pan immediately.

title: baked cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in buttered casserole dish.
Beat eggs, salt and cream.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle grated cheese.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender in small amount of water.
Add milk, margarine, salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken with instant mashed potatoes.
Top with chopped parsley when serving.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain juice from one jar of artichokes into skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in juice.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed (lettuce, celery, onion, green pepper and peas).
Spread salad dressing (frosting). Sprinkle sugar over salad dressing.
Layer cheese and then bacon bits.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Serve!

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish with margarine.
Layer ingredients with chicken, celery, water chestnuts, noodles, onion and peppers in that order.
Repeat layers.
Saute almonds in a skillet with a little margarine and sprinkle on top of casserole. Mix soup with milk and pour over all.
Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix all the ingredients into a Texas size (large) pan. Cook at 250° for 2 hours. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix and fry as patties; may cover with mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese. Serves 6.

title: italian green beans
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in oil until slightly brown. Add beans, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Remove cover and add sliced tomato and mix well.
Lay potatoes on top.
Cover and cook over low heat until beans and potatoes are cooked, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
More water can be added if necessary.

title: herbed buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and let stand 5 minutes. Stir in mayonnaise until mixture is smooth, season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate. Makes 2 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well together.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cook at 500° for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix well with the celery, onions and salad dressing. Mix shrimp in last.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Bring to boil and pour over pickles in jar.
Seal, cool and then put in
refrigerator.
Can
eat
next day.
Put dill, garlic, onion and grape leaf or two in jar.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: top ramen cabbage salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds in a 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Break up the noodles; do not cook.
Mix cabbage, onions and noodles and all dressing.

title: coco-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease one 9X13 inch baking pan. Sift the flour, sugar and baking soda together. In a saucepan over medium heat, bring one cup of the butter, 3 Tbsp. of the cocoa, and one cup of the cola drink to a boil. Pour into the flour mixture and stir in the marshmallows, buttermilk, and the beaten eggs. Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove cake from oven and top with Coco-Cola Icing while cake is still warm.

title: delicious apple muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, gradually adding sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add chopped apples and stir just enough to mix.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Place wedge of apple dipped into sugar on top of each muffin.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: kentucky chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper. Dip cut up chicken pieces into butter, then bread crumb mixture. Coat well.
Arrange in shallow pan, then pour remaining butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender basting frequently with drippings.
Do not turn chicken.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: ooddles of noodles
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain any fat. Add remaining ingredients, except for cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in Wesson oil.
Add ground beef and cook until done.
Drain juice off beans.
Add beans, chili powder and salt.
Add tomato juice.
Cook on low in a covered pan about 20 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Combine flour, onion, red pepper, horseradish and salt; stir in 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Cook until bubbly, then remove from heat.
Add milk and cook until thickens; stir constantly. Add hot sauce a little at a time to egg yolks, stirring briskly. Combine egg mixture with remaining sauce.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and crab meat.
Mix well.
Serve in clean crab shells or custard cups.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar together in bowl.
Add egg; mix well.
Blend in milk.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in separate bowl.
Add to butter mixture.
Spread half of the batter in greased 8-inch round baking dish; cover with 3/4 can of pie filling.
Spread the remaining batter; top with remaining pie filling.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together. Chill. Roll into balls and then roll in powdered sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: b.b.q. spare ribs
directions: Mix bbq sauce with soy sauce, ham and hickory smoked salt. Put ribs in a slow cooker and add this mixture to it and stir. cook on low 9-10 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: meghan's cornflake crunchies
directions: First you take cornflakes.
Then you melt chocolate, and I think you put them in the microwave for about 15 minutes.
Then you take them out, and you eat them.
Eat them with a napkin and a plate.
Eat them with juice.

title: orange crush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except Orange Crush and ginger ale.
Set aside to cool.
Add Orange Crush and ginger ale just before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put 1 box of pudding in bowl.
Add juice from pineapple and oranges.
Mix well.
Add container of Cool Whip; stir.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Put in refrigerator and let set.
Before serving, chip 2 bananas in this.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: bunny's split pea soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender.
Brown chopped onions in butter and add to the soup.
Gradually add 1 quart of milk and heat through.

title: egg bake
directions: Put layer of sausage in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with cheese. Beat 10 eggs, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over cheese. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice according to directions. Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese; add in milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust and chill 3 hours.
Top with strawberries and glaze.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix syrup, milk and butter together; heat until butter melts. Set aside to cool.

title: parmesan squash
directions: Place onion and butter in bowl; microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased bowl.
Microwave on High 14 to 19 minutes or until set, rotating 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Let set 8 to 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend flour, sugar, cinnamon and butter with blender or fork until flaky.
Arrange apples in baking dish; sprinkle flour and sugar mixture over the top of the apples.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until the apples are done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rinse saucepan with cold water; do not dry.
Pour in milk and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in rice, return to boil. Lower heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until rice is tender (about 1 hour).

title: larry's barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan on medium heat.
Stir constantly until well blended.
Simmer 1/2 hour minimum.

title: owen's frosting
directions: Melt chocolate.
Beat egg yolks until very thick.
Add sugar, milk and butter to egg yolks.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate, salt and vanilla.
Beat until it will spread nicely.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies(3 to 4 dozen)
directions: Mix in saucepan milk, cocoa, oil and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper to cool.

title: katie foster's easy coconut cake
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions.
Put cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan to cook.
While cake is still warm, poke holes in top of cake with a fork.
Shake cream of coconut well and pour over hot cake while still in pan (use entire can).
After cake cools in pan, ice with Cool Whip and sprinkle additional coconut on top.

title: grandma's french biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt on a biscuit board. Add lard and butter; mash thoroughly together.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add milk, then stir in flour mixture.
Mix to a good consistency.
Knead as little as possible.
Roll out on biscuit board; cut thick, then put in baking pan.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 to 17 minutes.
Yields approximately 30.

title: easy english trifle
directions: Slice pound cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Line bottom of a 16-cup trifle bowl or large serving bowl with one-third of the cake slices.
Spread strawberries over cake slices.
Spoon half of the pudding over strawberries; place half of the remaining cake slices over pudding.
Gently spread strawberry preserves over cake layer; top with remaining cake slices.
Spoon remaining pudding on top.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Spread Cool Whip on top; garnish with strawberries.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Saute cabbage, celery and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Spoon into 2 quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until heated.

title: teresa's french toast - orange
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Dip bread in mixture; cook in a nonstick skillet until done.
Squeeze fresh orange juice over toast; sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: glorious mashed potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes (cut up) until tender.
Drain and mash until smooth.
Then mix in other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Put in refrigerator until 15 minutes before serving.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: frosted creams
directions: Sift the flour and spices.
Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add the egg.
Put the 1 teaspoon of soda in boiling water.
Add the molasses and syrup.
Add the soda and water alternately with flour. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out of the center of cake clean.
Frost with a light icing or serve with whipped cream.

title: cherry nuggets
directions: Combine blueberry mix, sugar and eggs.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Spread in greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 12 bars.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Fold in milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Do not cover. Top with the butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chinese fried shrimp and rice
directions: Brown shrimp in oil.
Add rice; brown lightly while stirring. Add onion; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs, soy sauce and salt. Cook and stir until eggs are set.
Garnish and serve.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: durango cottage cheese and vegetable dip(makes 2 cups; under 100 calories)
directions: Place cottage cheese in electric blender container; whirl until smooth.
Spoon into bowl; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into serving bowl; cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Use as a dip with raw vegetables.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Simmer 2/3 cup water and 1 cup berries for 3 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water.
Blend into hot mixture. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Save 1/2 cup choice berries.
Put 2 1/2 cups berries in baked pie shell.
Cover with cooked berry mixture.
Garnish with berries.

title: pecans delight
directions: Press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool crust.

title: biscuit ready mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients together several times until well blended.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until like coarse meal.
Store in airtight container.

title: walnut orange loaves
directions: With electric mixer, cream butter with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternately with orange juice and bourbon. Stir in dates, walnuts and ground up orange.
Bake in 2 loaf pans that have been buttered and floured.
350° approx. 45 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Use apple pulp left from preparing apple juice for jelly. Press through sieve or food mill. Measure pulp. Add sugar and spices.
Cook until the flavors are well blended, about 15 minutes, to prevent sticking.
Stir frequently as mixture thickens (if too thick, add a small amount of water to desired consistency).
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: three layer pie
directions: Combine flour, butter and pecans for crust.
Pat into oblong Pyrex.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip for first layer.
Combine milk and puddings for second layer.
Top with Cool Whip for third layer.

title: salad dressing
directions: Melt butter, then add flour.
Add vinegar and water to butter and flour.
Add sugar and beaten egg and cook 5 minutes, stirring while it is cooking.
Add mustard and salt.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add egg yolks and milk.
Mix and add butter.
Cook on High in microwave for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes more; stir.
Keep repeating this step, cooking 3 to 4 minutes and stirring until thick.
Add vanilla; stir.
Put into already baked pie shell.
Top with meringue which needs to be browned in regular oven.

title: hoppin john
directions: Soak peas overnight, drain, rinse and put in kettle.
Cover with boiling water.
Add the soda and bring to a boil.
Drain and rinse again.
Now, put in fresh water and boil, allowing a quart and a half water; add the salt and meat.
Cook just at boiling point for 4 hours.
Now, add the rice and boil 45 minutes longer.

title: field mice pie
directions: Cook all ingredients together and place in a casserole lined with pie dough.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
If no field mice are available, 1 pound of pork sausage may be used. This recipe was taken from an old pioneer cookbook.

title: caramel pull-apart pecan rolls
directions: Cut each loaf of thawed bread into 16 equal pieces and set aside.
In medium bowl, combine pudding mix, pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well; space half of the bread pieces unevenly on bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour 1/2 of melted butter over them; sprinkle with 1/2 of butterscotch mixture.
Place the rest of bread pieces among first ones.
Cover with remaining butter and mixture.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or cover loosely and place in refrigerator overnight.
Risen dough should reach to top of pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown and puffed.
Remove from oven and immediately invert on cookie sheet or large rectangular tray.
Serve warm.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and cook until crisp.
Drain, but save bacon fat to fry onions (chopped) until they are clear but not brown.
Remove onions from pan.
Saute mushrooms in butter or bacon fat.
Combine bacon, onions, mushrooms, and sauerkraut with undiluted mushroom soup.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Ready to eat, or can be baked for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked lentils with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 11 ingredients in a shallow 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover tightly and bake 30 minutes. Uncover and stir in carrots and celery.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in green pepper and parsley. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: deviled deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and blend in remaining ingredients.
Re-fill whites.
Makes 12.
Prep time:
25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash potatoes and slice thin.

In greased 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes in four layers, sprinkling each of the first 3 layers with 1 tablespoon onion, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and 1 tablespoon butter. Add cheese on the very top.
Heat milk to scalding.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 1 hour until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: granny's original pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, stir in other ingredients and pour into pie shell. Top with pecan halves if you have them.
Bake at 305° for about 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when stuck in center of pie.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in large Cool Whip.
Layer with graham crackers in large pan.

title: kona inn banana bread
directions: Stir and toss flour, salt, baking soda, powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, mix shortening, sugar, bananas, eggs and walnuts.
Add the dry ingredients and stir until well blended. Pour into 2 prepared loaf pans and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse in cold water.
Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes, together.
Add to spaghetti.
Marinate overnight.
Put cubed tomatoes on top before serving.

title: coconut tart
directions: Press into a 7 x 11 inch pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: lemon syrup
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes and add to juice and rind. Use for instant lemonade.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with one cup hot water.
Mix gelatin in small amount of cold water.
Add to jello mixture and mix well.
Add milk. Chill about 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for about 2 hours.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples, together until well blended.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, slice and cook yellow squash and onion. Drain.
Combine squash, onion, sour cream, soup and Cheddar cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Sprinkle on top of squash mixture and bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: eggplant-sesame dip(arabic)
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (205°C).
Use a fork to pierce eggplant in several places.
Place pierce eggplant on oven rack and bake 3/4 hour or until soft.
Cool.
Peel.
Dice pulp into a blender or food processor.
Add sesame seed paste, oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Process until mixture is smooth and pale.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Garnish with parsley and/or pomegranate seeds, if desired.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate almond chiffon pie
directions: In a double boiler, place the almond bars, bitter chocolate or envelope of Choco-bake, large marshmallows and milk.
Let this dissolve; stir often.
Let cool, then fold in the whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator. Ready to serve; add whipped cream topping around edge.

title: sun tea
directions: Put tea bags in jar of water.
Cover top of jar; let set outside in sun for 1 to 2 hours or until well darkened and sugar to taste.

title: sherry orange slices(8 servings)
directions: Pare oranges, cutting deep enough to remove all white membrane.
Cut into thin slices.
Arrange each slice orange on salad greens.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Drizzle slices with sherry and top with coconut.

title: snowflake pudding
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, gelatin and salt.
Add milk.
Stir over medium heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add vanilla.
Fold in coconut, then whipped cream.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 6 hours.
(It can be baked overnight in a 200° oven.)
After it is cooked, let it sit for about 1/2 hour and then shred the meat, removing the fat.
This can then be stored in the refrigerator until needed (can make a day ahead of time). Bake in sauce for another hour until bubbly. Serves 32.

title: hollywood punch
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: chicken and cornbread dressing
directions: Cook chicken in large pot with salt until it comes off bones. Take out of pot; remove bones and skin.
In the broth, put 1 can cream of chicken soup, onion, sage and pepper.
Add cornbread and biscuits; stir all of this together.
Stir in chicken.
Pour into baking pan; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with giblet gravy made from 2 boiled eggs and the giblets from the chicken.
Mix in 1 can cream of chicken soup.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender; serve over crushed ice.
Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut crisps(zelnik)
directions: Crumble flour, lard and salt like for pie crust.
Add small can of sauerkraut with juice.
Divide dough in two rolls like for pie crust; put on oiled cookie sheet.
Press out with fingers real thin like for pizza.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Cracklings may be added.

title: colcannon
directions: Chop the cooked cabbage.
Chop up onion tops and simmer them in milk to just cover until they are soft.
Drain and mash the potatoes.
Season and beat well.
Then add cooked leeks and milk.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until brown (this is the cornbread).
Mix all remaining ingredients; add cooked cornbread.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Pour 1 cup broth over top and cook for 30 minutes.

title: pork normandy
directions: Brown pork chops and lay in baking dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: absent cook's stew
directions: Place beef, peeled and sliced carrots, onions and quartered potatoes in a heavy roasting pan with a lid.
Combine tomato soup, water, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over meat and vegetables and cover with close fitting lid.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour over thawed hash browns.
Mix lightly.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1/4 cup melted margarine and 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Cut water chestnuts in 1/2.
Soak in soy sauce for a couple of hours.
Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and secure with toothpick.
Broil until almost done cooking bacon.
Cool.
Then roll into brown sugar.
Finish cooking bacon.
Serve warm.

title: puree of carrot soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil and add carrots, onion, celery, potato, garlic and sugar.
Cover and cook vegetables over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the cloves, pepper and broth and bring the soup to a boil.
Reduce the heat and cook the soup, partially covering the pan for about 20 minutes or until the vegetables are soft.
Remove and discard the cloves. Puree the soup in batches in a blender or food processor.

title: senior prom punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up thoroughly.
Combine chilled juice in a large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Serve in punch cups or in hollow stemmed glasses.
Makes about 40 servings.

title: quick and easy barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: forget me not cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add salt and continue to beat. Gradually add sugar, beating the egg whites to form stiff peaks. Fold in pecans and chocolate pieces.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Put into a preheated oven at 350°.
Turn oven off after placing cookies in.
Leave cookies in oven overnight.
Do not open door until morning.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs one at a time.
Beat in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in raisins or nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together until blended.
Put a vanilla wafer, flat side up, in the bottom of a small foil or paper baking cup (2 to 2 1/2-inch cups work best). Top with cheese mixture (fill each one 3/4 full).
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with a teaspoon of pie filling.

title: ice cream pineapple pie
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, sugar and margarine in a 9-inch pie pan; mix well.
With back of tablespoon, press crumb mixture evenly and firmly around sides and bottom of pie pan.
Chill. Pour milk into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and ice cream; beat on low for 1 to 2 minutes, or until well beaten.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Add shortening and sugar to warm applesauce.
Add spices and salt to flour.
Mix a little flour to raisins and nuts to keep them from sticking together.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until tested with straw.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dust chicken with flour; brown chicken in oil.
Add soup, wine, onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cover; cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more or until done. Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: impossible taco pie(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Spray 10 inch pie plate with Pam.
Cook turkey and onions, stir in seasoning mix and cook to blend. Spread in pie plate and top with chilies.
Beat together skim milk, bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over turkey mixture. Bake 25 minutes, top with tomatoes and cheese, continue baking until knife inserted in center comes out clean (8-10 minutes). Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Each serving equals:
1/2 bread, 3 proteins, 1 1/2 vegetable.

title: broccoli & cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon until evenly brown, drain, crumble and set aside. Combine bacon, cauliflower, broccoli, onion and sunflower seeds. Whisk together the salad dressing, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad and toss to coat.
Refrigerate and allow to chill before serving.

title: loudell pafford sizemore's pig sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat.
Use to baste meat while cooking.
This sauce goes great with a cooked pig.
Also good on any grilled pork.

title: famous lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch	and
sugar.
Cover with grated rind and juice of lemons.	Add
beaten
yolks of eggs; then add boiling water. Cook until thick; pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat 6 tablespoons of sugar into
them.
Spread over lemon mixture.
Take care to seal in filling
completely.
Bake	in
oven
at
for 15 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Fill greased and floured muffin tins, 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes.
Place on racks to cool.
Serve with butter, honey or cream cheese.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat; blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk; heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.

title: appleless apple pie
directions: Bring water,
sugar and cream of tartar to a boil, then add crackers;
boil
for
minutes.
Cool
a	little before putting in	pie
shell.
Bake
at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: grilled red snapper
directions: Prepare grill.
Rinse fish in cold water.
Pat dry.
Sprinkle inside and out with salt and pepper.
Drizzle cavities with oil and stuff with lemon slices and herbs.
Grill, turning once, until just opaque at backbone, about 15 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in jar (1 gallon).
Heat sugar, salt, spices and vinegar just until sugar melts.
Pour this mixture over cucumbers and onions to fill jar.

title: chicken fontanelli
directions: Cook fresh spinach (boil in pot).
Take chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan with aluminum foil; pour Italian dressing.
Drain spinach and top chicken.
Add Fontanelli cheese on top.
Put aluminum foil over dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 4 servings.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all the ingredients.
Pour into one 9-inch pastry shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake about 25 minutes more.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Lightly oil oblong Pyrex dish.
Spread cherries over bottom and sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Cut thin pats of margarine and lay side by side, covering entire cake mix.
Top with pecans. Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Leave uncovered until completely cooled.
Excellent after refrigerated.

title: betty black's secret nut cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter together.
Beat eggs separately (whites and yellows).
Stir them into mixture.
Add 3 cups flour, which has been sifted only once.
Take the remaining cup of flour and dredge nuts and raisins.
Line bottom of the cake pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: talaharina
directions: Brown
beef
and
onions while cooking noodles.
Drain. In large bowl, mix all the ingredients plus salt and pepper to taste. Put
in
large
casserole
dish.
Cook until bubbly at 350°. Just before removing, add more cheese for topping.

title: pickle roll-up appetizers
directions: Mix enough mayonnaise with the tub of cream cheese to make it a good spreading consistency.
Add onion to taste.
Cut the crusts off the bread and roll each slice flat.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread slices.
Dry the pickles and place one on each bread slice and roll up.
Roll each up in
a piece of waxed paper and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Slice each roll into pieces and serve.

title: chocolate brittle
directions: Melt butter and combine with sugar; bring to rolling boil. Boil for a few minutes.
Pour mixture over saltines on a jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turn off oven and remove pan.
Distribute chocolate morsels over saltines.
Return pan to oven; morsels will melt.
Remove pan and spread chocolate and top with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate until chocolate is solid.
Break into pieces and enjoy.

title: onion bread fritters
directions: Mix flour and meal together with salt and soda.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Stir well (if too thick, add water).
Add chopped onion; stir well.
Heat oil in skillet (just cover the bottom to fry first batch).
Dip 2 tablespoons batter into hot oil for each fritter.
Watch and turn with spatula until done.

title: banana-pineapple yogurt shake
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients except ice. Blend until smooth.
With blender running, add ice cubes one at a time through opening in lid, blending until slushy.
Pour into glasses.
Makes 4 (7 ounce) servings.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Saute rice in oil over medium heat for 15 minutes or more, until golden brown.
Add meat, if desired.
Heat through.
Pour beaten eggs over rice.
Cook, stirring often, until the eggs are set.
Sprinkle with the onion and the soy sauce mixed with the sugar, pepper and salt.
Stir just until blended.

title: taco dish
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together, except Bisquick and water.
Mix Bisquick and water and spread in baking dish.
Pour mixture over Bisquick.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with chips and salsa.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream well. Add eggs and flour; beat well.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: baked catfish(low-fat)
directions: Mix all spices and meal; dredge fish in mix.
Spray oil on fish.
Place fish in center.
Fold foil securely and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until flaky.

title: sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Brown sausage or use Little Smokies.
Simmer in beer 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out sausage.
Mix all ingredients into beer.
Add sausage.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: tasty beef roll-ups
directions: Coat each steak (rec. 2 per serving) with flour, eggs and then bread crumbs on each side.
Set aside.
Place 1 slice of cheese and 1 slice of ham on each steak.
Starting from one end, roll up and secure with a toothpick.
When done, brown each side of roll-up in a frying pan with oil.
Now, place each roll-up in a baking dish in the oven.
Set at 375° for about 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with brown gravy, mashed potatoes and vegetable.

title: peachy blueberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse blueberries from mix, rinse with cold water and drain.
Arrange peach slices in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle blueberries over peaches.
Combine water and brown sugar in liquid measuring cup.
Pour over fruit.
Combine muffin mix, pecans and melted butter in large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
(Mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit.
Sprinkle contents of topping packet from mix over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve warm with warm whipped topping, if deserved.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until completely mixed.
Refrigerate.
Cover tightly.
Keep no longer than 4 weeks.
Serve on fruit or tossed salad.

title: melt in your mouth sausages or spaghetti topping
directions: Place sausage in skillet and cover with water.
Simmer for 10 minutes; drain.
Discard water.
Place remaining ingredients in slow cooker; add drained sausage, cut in small pieces.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours, then increase temperature to high and cook 1 hour more.
Serve in buns or over cooked spaghetti. Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Dip chicken in mixture, then in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Arrange in buttered flat baking dish. Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well in large container.
Keep tightly sealed in jars.
Fill cup 1/2 full with chocolate mixture; add boiling water to fill cup and stir well.

title: rice pudding
directions: Steam rice per directions on package.
Combine steamed rice, egg mixture and 2 quarts of milk.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Alternating, add vanilla wafer crumbs and milk, a little at a time, ending with the wafers.
Add coconut and pecans and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake seems to be done after testing with knife blade in center of cake.
Let cool in the pan.

title: chocolate candy balls
directions: Melt chocolate and wax together in double boiler.
Keep warm on low heat.
Mix remaining ingredients; form into balls.
Dip them into chocolate mixture.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan. Add onion and cook until golden yellow. Stir in sauerkraut and cook for 8 minutes.
Mix in potato and caraway seed.
Pour in the boiling water.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 30 minutes. Cover and continue cooking 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Put salt and pecans together in a jar.
Fill jar with warm water.
Let stand in warm water for 30 minutes, then drain 2 hours in colander.
Cook at 275° for 30 minutes.
Cut oven off (leave pecans in oven).
Stir 3 or 4 times.
You may use salt, garlic salt or both to taste.
Very good.

title: carbonara plus
directions: Cook bacon over medium high heat for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms. Stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add meat and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add pasta; toss to mix and heat through.
Turn off heat. Beat eggs, cream and Parmesan.
Pour over mixture and toss. Serve at once.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat egg and 3/4 cup milk together.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Roll thin; cut in strips and drop in boiling broth. After dumplings have cooked, add 1/2 cup milk.
Remove from heat after it comes to a boil.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute 1 onion, garlic, meat and bell pepper.
Add spices, vinegar and canned tomatoes.
Simmer until thick or add thickening.

title: play dough a la peanut butter(shape, decorate and eat)
directions: In medium bowl with large spoon combine peanut butter and honey.
Add dry milk until you have the consistency of play dough.
Shape.
Decorate with raisins, peanuts, cake decorations, chocolate chips, M&M's (use your imagination).
Have fun.
For the young at heart.

title: easy funfetti cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, drop by rounded spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: monster oatmeal cookie
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour, soda, oats and raisins.
Pat into a 9-inch circle on a greased pizza pan.
Bake on upper rack for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut while warm or break apart while cool.

title: d & m's pie crust to freeze
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt together.
Add Karo and water. Makes 24 pie crusts.
Roll into balls enough for 1 pie crust.
Put each one in a freezer bag.
Freeze.
Take out as needed.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat egg; add sugar.
While beating, add flour with baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and flavorings.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan with greased bottom.
Cover with layer of peeled and cored apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for roughly 25 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: curried chicken balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except egg and the one cup of bread crumbs.
Shape into 24 balls.
Dip balls in beaten egg and then roll in one cup of bread crumbs.
Arrange 12 pieces in a circle on a paper plate and microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 3 to 4 minutes, or until heated through.
Repeat procedure with remaining 12 pieces.
Serve with curry-flavored mayonnaise.

title: apple fritters
directions: You will need an electric skillet or fry on stove.

title: pearl frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Beat until smooth with mixer at low speed.
Store, covered, at room temperature.
Good for cookies!

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion.
Stir in chuck, garlic, flour, salt, pepper, paprika and mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley or other herbs.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: calico pickles
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Dissolve salt in water and pour over vegetables.
Soak for 15 to 18 hours in a cool place.
Drain.
In a large kettle, mix sugar, spices and vinegar. Bring to a boil and boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Pack hot into 8 hot pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles.
Adjust caps; process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield:
8 pints.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add cocoa and sugar to butter. Heat mixture for a few minutes on medium stirring thoroughly. Slowly add cream and cook until bubbly. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour over your favorite ice cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and spice to taste.
Place corn into hamburger alternating Tater Tots and hamburger mixture; place into baking dish.
Take 2 cans Cheddar cheese soup and place over mixture. Last, place three cups Cheddar cheese on top of everything.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double chocolate mint bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat in eggs and 1/4 teaspoon mint extract; spread into pan and bake 23 to 25 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt 1/2 cup oleo with chocolate chips.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and remaining 1/4 teaspoon mint extract.
Pour over baked layer and let stand in refrigerator until set.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine in large bowl and chill.
Add dressing.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish; cool slightly.
Pour rice over margarine.
Arrange chicken over rice; sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Mix chicken soup with water.
Pour over casserole.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and cinnamon into dish.
Add egg, milk and melted shortening to dish. Stir in chopped apples.
Pour into greased pan and top with hard butter, 5 tablespoons flour and 5 tablespoon sugar, all chopped together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apricot baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Arrange chicken in a 2-quart utility dish with larger pieces at the corners of the dish, skin side down.
Place small pieces in the center of the dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Spread this mixture over chicken. Cover with waxed paper or microwave plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 12 to 14 minutes until chicken is tender.
Halfway through, turn chicken pieces over and lightly stir sauce.
Watch closely when nearing end of cooking time that sauce doesn't become too thick or scorched.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: low-fat shrimp vera cruz
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients except cheese and parsley. Transfer to small microwave dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave on High 1 minute or until heated through and cheese melts.
Garnish with parsley.

title: papa's baked beans
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° or microwave 5 to 7 minutes on High, stirring once.

title: banana-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Slice bananas into blender. Whir until pureed (1 cup). Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Cream butter with sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, vanilla and pureed bananas. Beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by heaping measuring tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Smooth top slightly. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges begin to brown.
Remove to rack to cool.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: methodist pie
directions: Roll crackers; mix sugar and butter together.
Add cracker crumbs and mix well.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Cook in greased muffin tins.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Does not have to rise.

title: easy pork chops and dressing
directions: Flour the chops and brown on both sides in melted shortening in skillet.
Put half of the pork chops on the bottom of casserole dish.
Make the Stove Top stuffing according to package directions and cover chops in the casserole dish.
Place remaining chops on top.
Mix the gravy according to the package directions, adding the bouillon cube for flavor.
Pour the gravy evenly over all. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in freezer until congealed.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except olive oil, salt and pepper. Stuff into artichoke leaves. Place artichoke in half a pan of water. Pour olive oil over artichoke and season with salt and pepper to taste. Cook artichoke on medium heat for approximately 1 hour or until tender.

title: quick drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix everything and serve.
Have everything chilled and add ice as needed.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter
and sugar; beat in eggs, salt and vanilla. Add flour and
soda.
Then add bananas and nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: frosted cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, 1/3 cup sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, egg and 1 1/2 cups of each flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough of the remaining flours to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes). Place in a greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (90 minutes).
Grease two oblong cake pans.

title: purple cow
directions: Put all ingredients in blender on medium.
Put lid on the blender.
Blend well.
Pour and drink.

title: mom's coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Add pineapple, apple juice, apples and Miracle Whip.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes.

title: good chili
directions: Melt lard or drippings in large pot over medium heat.
Add onion; cook until translucent.
Add meat and garlic; cook until meat is brown.
Add tomato sauce, red chile peppers, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Stir to coat meat.
Add water to cover meat. Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/4 hours, stirring frequently.
Add water as needed to prevent liquid from cooking away.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma's old fashion bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread.
Soak in a little water or 1/2 of milk for about 15 minutes.
Mash out all lumps.
Add eggs, sugar, milk, raisins and vanilla.
Mix to a smooth pudding.
Pour in a greased pan and bake until nice and brown.
Serve hot or cool.

title: old-fashioned chess pie
directions: Beat
eggs
until light.
Add sugar and butter and beat again. Add
remaining
ingredients
and
pour into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake
until brown or about 35 to 40 minutes in 300° oven.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy. Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Fold in nuts, chocolate chips, apples and vanilla until evenly distributed. Spoon into greased and floured pan. Bake in 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes until cakes test done.

title: chicken 'n' ritz
directions: Place chicken on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and place on top of chicken.
Crush crackers and place on top of soups.
Melt butter and spread over crackers.
Bake about 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: dogs in a sweater
directions: You will need 8 popsicle sticks.

title: lip-smacking wings
directions: Combine chicken with remaining ingredients.
Marinate at least 1 1/2 hours.
Dredge in flour and fry in hot oil until brown.

title: betty browns
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except apples and nuts.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into about 18 squares.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Stir and simmer until celery and onion are cooked.
In a small pan, melt margarine or butter. Add flour; stir to remove lumps.
Add milk to make a smooth sauce. Add cheese; heat gently until thickened, stirring constantly. Add potato mixture.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil these ingredients: sugar, Wesson oil, vinegar, celery salt, salt and garlic.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cinnamon leaf ring
directions: Cool milk to lukewarm (110°); sprinkle yeast over top.
Let stand to soften.
Cream shortening and 1/4 cup butter; add 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, yeast mixture and enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic on lightly floured cloth or board.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour. Divide dough in half.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Dip each round in melted butter and then in combined 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 2 cups sugar.
Place rounds on end in 2 well-buttered 8 1/2-inch ring molds.
Let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans on racks a few minutes.
Turn out on racks.
Makes 2 coffee cakes.

title: three step chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix until blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chips, nuts, fresh fruit or whipped topping.

title: breakfast brunch ham souffle
directions: Cube bread and ham.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread, ham and cheese. You may top with buttered corn flakes, if you wish.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sheila's egg noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef and drain.
Add chopped onions, green peppers and pizza sauce.
Bring to a medium boil; remove from heat.
Add noodles to beef mixture.
Mix well!
Spread in a large casserole dish.
Cover with marble cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese has melted.
Remove from oven.

title: dirt salad
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and cookies.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain, cool, peel and shred.
Cook 2 cups cheese and butter in saucepan over low heat until almost melted, stirring constantly (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Pour into buttered dish (one 9 x 13-inch or two 8 x 8-inch).
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
(This recipe also works good when frozen, then thawed before baking.)

title: chicken a la jill
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper and pound slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add green onions, lemon juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Whisk in broth and stir until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the meats and season with salt and pepper.
Add eggs and rice and mix well.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, white sugar, sweet milk and cocoa in pot.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
When full boil is reached, cook for one minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool and eat.

title: tabooley salad
directions: Cover cracked wheat with cold water; let stand 30 minutes. Drain the water; press out as much water as possible.
It is best to take handfuls and squeeze the water out.

title: salt substitute recipe
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keep in covered spice bottle or jar.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions in a food processor or blender.
Take out most of the seeds before chopping.
You may want to wear a pair of gloves to keep from getting the hot on your hands or in your eyes.
Put all the ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil for 30 minutes.
Pour into small jars and seal.

title: oyster stew
directions: Remove oysters from liquor.
Heat liquor to boiling point. Add oysters and cook until edges curl, few minutes.
Put in milk, seasonings and butter.
Serve hot.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Combine ground beef mixture, cheese, soup, jalapenos, onion and tomato in crock-pot; mix well.
Heat until cheese is melted.
May add a small amount of milk if desired. Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Yield:
128 servings.

title: boiled cake(100 year old recipe)
directions: Place shortening, sugar, spices and raisins in saucepan.
Pour hot water over.
Add baking soda and bring to a boil; cool.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder; blend well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add salt, sugar, milk and vanilla. Butter an unbaked pie shell.
Pour custard in shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, 325° for 25 minutes.

title: parsleyed potatoes
directions: Prepare and cook potatoes as directed.
Cook until tender. Before serving, toss with butter and sprinkle with parsley.

title: chili spaghetti
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is no longer pink; drain. Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until spaghetti is just tender. Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: chile-sausage squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and mayonnaise; stir well.
Spread mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla to milk.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together.
Add dry ingredients with milk to mixture.
Pour in boiling water all at once.
Stir until mixed.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° until well set.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: world's best tea cakes
directions: Mix oil,
margarine,
sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating well after each.
Slowly add flour, salt, baking soda and mix well.
Chill dough 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator. Preheat oven to
Shape
dough in 1-inch balls, space 2-inches apart
on
ungreased
cookie
sheets.
Flatten cookies with glass dipped
in
sugar.
Bake
about
15 minutes until lightly browned at the edge.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: pecan snacks
directions: Heat corn oil in heavy skillet over moderate heat.
Add pecans, onion powder and garlic salt.
Stir constantly 1 minute. Remove from heat and drain on paper towel.

title: biscuit lasagne
directions: Mix and simmer first 5 ingredients 20 minutes.
Separate biscuits.
Press each to 4-inch circle.
Mix cheeses and seasoning together and place 2 tablespoons on each biscuit.
Fold over and seal.
Place meat mixture in baking dish, then biscuits on top and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Place cranberries, nuts and orange rind in a bowl and set aside.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in orange juice, eggs and orange rind.
Mix just to moisten.
Fold in cranberries, nuts and orange rind mixture.
Spoon into well-greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put a square of waxed paper inside pie shell and fill with dried beans, rice or pie weights.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until dough looks set.
Remove beans and waxed paper. Prick the dough with fork; continue baking 10 minutes longer.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 stick butter, onions and celery.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli with soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add to celery and onion.
Stir in rice.
Put in greased casserole pan.
Melt butter with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket(german)
directions: Season hamburger with salt and pepper.
Add egg, mixing well. Mix in rice.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well together.
Store in sealed container.
Mix 1/3 cup mix per 1 cup hot water.

title: yankee noodle dandies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels, wax and peanut butter in double boiler.
Pour mixture over nuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon on wax or foil paper.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot and cover with water. Simmer until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Great for a slow cooker.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix well the sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add the dry jello and fold in fruit.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: lemonade jello ring
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Add this juice (maximum of 3/4 cup) plus enough water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid; boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling juice/water.
Add lemonade.
Chill until syrupy and then whip.
Whip the thawed Cool Whip and add the Jell-O mixture.
Add the pineapple.
Pour into bowl or ring mold and refrigerate.
Can garnish the center of mold with strawberries or raspberries.

title: pickle beets
directions: Wash; do not peel. Cook beets until tender and skin slips. Mix sugar, water, vinegar and pickling spices. Bring to a boil. Pour over packed beets. Process 30 minutes in hot water bath. Syrup for about 6 pints.

title: poppy bread(polish; 2 loaves)
directions: *The salt, though traditional, may be eliminated if you choose to do so.

title: papaya sunriser
directions: Chill 4 tall glasses in the freezer.
Cut papaya and banana into chunks.
Combine papaya, banana, yogurt and orange juice in blender container.
Whirl on high for 30 seconds.
Add ice.
Blend for 30 seconds more.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Float 1 tablespoon of grenadine on each, if desired.

title: mangu (mashed green plantain)(dominican republic style)
directions: Plantains are easily peeled if cut lengthwise and crosswise first.
If peeled under water no stain will remain on hands.
They can be boiled with skin.
This is frequently done in N. Y., but this makes the pot harder to clean.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir until blended.
Spoon into crumb crusts.
Freeze at least 8 hours.
Garnish with dollops of whipped topping, if desired.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, cut up marshmallows and add 1 1/2 cups of hot
water.
Put
in refrigerator until it begins to jell. Add whipping
cream (it should already be whipped), pineapple and nuts.
Return to refrigerator until completely congealed.

title: salt dough decorations
directions: Mix all ingredients completely with hands (if dough is too dry, work in 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons water).
Form shapes as desired.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside.
Cook yellow rice without butter.
Chop onion and pepper.
While rice is hot, add cheese. Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs.
Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with crumb mixture.
Mix together sausage and remaining ingredients; pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until brown.

title: oatmeal layer fudge-nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread 3/4 of mixture on greased cookie sheet.

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Stir all together.
Turn crock-pot on high and cook 4 hours with lid on.
Remove lid and stir occasionally.
Remove lid and stir occasionally during an additional 4 to 6 hours of cooking time with the lid off.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add nuts and raisins. Beat eggs. Add to milk which has soda dissolved in. Add oleo and vanilla. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and extract.
Add together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add food coloring.
Press cookies with tree design onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and sliced mushrooms.
Cook five minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut and slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add salt.
Let stand for at least 3 hours.
Then drain off juices.
Put remaining ingredients in an agot pot and bring to a rolling boil.
Add drained cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Heat thoroughly and pack while hot in jars.
Seal at once.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Press in a 9-inch pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato dumplings(pennsylvania dutch recipe)
directions: Grate potatoes, place them in a cloth and squeeze out as much moisture as possible.
Work fast or the potatoes will darken.
Soak bread in cold water, then with the hands squeeze out as much water as possible.
Mix together the bread, salt, pepper, grated onions and parsley.
Add the grated potatoes and beaten eggs and mix well. Form into balls, roll gently in flour and drop into boiling water. Cover pan tightly and cook for 15 minutes.
Drain and serve.
Good with sauerkraut and stewed chicken or pot roast.

title: pork roast
directions: Mix soups and water. Pour over roast. Bake, covered at 350° until tender.

title: fluffy white frosting & chocolate cake
directions: Beat until thick.
Double for layer cake.

title: chess pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine; press into greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese together with electric mixer.
Cream until real smooth.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Shake ingredients together or blend in blender.
May be stored.
Mix enough with shredded cabbage to lightly moisten for great cole slaw.

title: shrimp gazpacho
directions: Rub wooden bowl with garlic.
Place shrimp into bowl; pour lemon juice in.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: jiffy orange nut bread
directions: Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Measure flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Melt butter or margarine in boiling water.
Blend in orange rind, juice, sugar, vanilla and slightly beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients over orange mixture; add nuts.
Stir just until all flour is dampened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour into a greased pan; place walnut halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain. Add beans, mushroom soup and tomato sauce.
Line bottom of casserole dish with bean mixture. Add layer of grated cheese, then layer of Doritos.
Continue layers, ending with cheese on top. Heat in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: chicken in lemon sauce
directions: Split chicken breasts, skin and remove bone.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add chicken.
Cook, turning, about 10 minutes or until chicken is brown and tender.
Remove chicken to ovenproof serving dish.
Discard butter from skillet.
Add wine, lemon peel and lemon juice to skillet; cook and stir over medium heat 1 minute.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Gradually pour in cream, stirring constantly, until hot; do not boil.
Pour cream sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Broil about 6 inches from heat source until lightly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small patties and fry in oil.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour
and
butter until smooth.
Then add syrup, eggs and pecans.
Add vanilla last.
Mix well and pour into cooked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat
and bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla; beat well.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Just before brownies are done, in a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and remaining vanilla.
Spread over brownies. Cool; chill and cut into bars.
Makes 36 to 40 brownies.

title: lemon poppy cake
directions: *May substitute orange rind and orange juice.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, 1 cup sugar, yogurt, butter and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and soda.
Do not overbeat.
Add berries; fill 12 greased and floured muffin tins. Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Dip warm muffins in 1/4 cup sugar.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop corn.
Put sugar, butter, cream of tartar and corn syrup on high heat and boil.
Stir in baking soda quickly.
(It foams and becomes brown in color.)
Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly.
Does not set fast (stays gooey).
Put on 2 large cookie sheets and bake 2 hours at 200°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix stuffing and butter. Spread some on lightly greased shallow baking pan (at least 2 1/2-quart capacity). Cover with layer of chicken; set aside. Mix broth and soups in pan. Stir and cook for 5 minutes. Spoon some over chicken. Repeat layers, ending with stuffing on top. Bake 45 minutes.

title: one bowl white bread
directions: Mix in basin or very large bowl, 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast and margarine.
