Pour water into dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 2 cups flour and beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Mix in enough flour (4 1/2 to 5 cups) to make soft dough.

title: squash casserole
directions: Blend sugar, margarine, flour, milk, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper in a double boiler.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Line baking dish with bread crumbs.
Pour squash mixture over crumbs. Sprinkle a few bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the potatoes with the milk and other ingredients.
Place in a 9-inch Pyrex dish.

title: skillet baptist cookies
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in skillet on low flame and stir until dates are melted.
Remove and add vanilla, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Let cool.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie plate.
Turn oven to 350°.
In blender, put coconut, sugar, salt, eggs, milk and flour.
Run the blender about 45 seconds.
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle well with nutmeg.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cook crushed pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add small box of Jell-O and 1 can of pie cherries (drained).
Cool.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells and top with Cool Whip.

title: betty talmadge's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll and cut.
Set aside 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter as biscuits start to brown.
Continue to bake until brown.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes more.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: philly cream cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems; chop enough stems to measure 1/2 cup. Cook half of mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons margarine over medium heat 5 minutes.
Drain.
Repeat with remaining mushroom caps and margarine.

title: apple butter-date cookies
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients, while allowing dates and raisins to soak in the apple butter.
In separate bowl, cream together oleo, sugar and egg.
Combine all mixtures; drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: daddy's chocolate fudge
directions: Using thick bottom pot, bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Boil for approximately 10 minutes (syrup should spin a thread).
Set pot off stove and add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until smooth (quickly).
Pour candy into buttered 14 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds of candy.
For thicker pieces use smaller pan.

title: fudge popsicles
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a medium size saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a rolling boil. Remove from heat; stir in Sweet 'N Low and salt, place in freezer until partly frozen, about 30 minutes.
Spoon mixture into medium size bowl; beat until smooth; pour into popsicle molds or 3 ounce paper cups.
Insert a stick into each popsicle.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients. Stir occasionally. Mix remaining ingredients together. Add melted mixture. Mix well until blended. Spread mixture evenly in 15-inch greased pan. Chill. Cut into bars.

title: licorice shake(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients for about 30 seconds in blender.
Serve in chilled glass.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all vegetables in large bowl.
Make dressing with all remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and let set in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch bake dish.
Mix margarine and dressing; sprinkle on top of vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french toast with hot cranberry butter
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt, sugar and butter.
Dip bread into mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Brown in fat in heavy skillet.
Serve with Hot Cranberry Butter.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Mix at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition. Blend in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Blend Spry, butter, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and pecans.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 25 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: bean and bacon soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
In large saucepan add soup, tomato sauce and meat.
Use one empty soup can and add milk (enough to make almost a full can).
Add to soup mixture.
Slowly allow to heat to desired temperature (no need to boil).
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Add crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until done.
Remove from bone and line casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and water chestnuts together.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and cover mixture.
Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.

title: smokie appetizers
directions: *If using large Smokie links, cut in thirds.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Put all chopped ingredients in large bowl; add dressing and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine in a mixing bowl the sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt; beat well.
Mix flour and soda; add to the first mixture and beat well.
Stir in the apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour in a tube pan which has been buttered and floured.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and add chili powder and paprika.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain grease off hamburger.
To hamburger, add chopped celery, onion and sliced tomatoes.
Add dressing to taste.
Mix in cheese and crunched Doritos and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and roll out into small circles.
Fill with pie filling and fry in Crisco oil in skillet.

title: hot mustard
directions: Blend mustard and vinegar in bowl.
Let stand covered at room temperature overnight.
Beat egg with sugar, salt and mustard mixture in saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Cool.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Serve as dipping sauce or spread for sandwiches.

title: taylorville beans
directions: Brown meat & drain well.
Combine all ingredients & bake uncovered for at least one hour at 350 degrees.
Can be cooked at 300-325 degrees for up to four hours.
Slow cooking for a longer time will result in the best flavor.

title: french salad in a bowl
directions: Rub salad bowl with clove garlic or use 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt.
Add salt, pepper, mustard and paprika.
Blend.
Beat in salad oil with fork.
Add salad greens and toss.
Sprinkle with vinegar and lemon juice and toss again.

title: chicken in a bag
directions: Wash and pat dry whole chicken.
Season to desired taste. Stuff with 1 orange and 1 lemon.
Put in paper bag.
(Bag should have no lettering.)
Cook for 1 hour at 450°.
Reduce to 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven.

title: cheddar cookies
directions: Cream butter. Stir in cheese, then stir in flour. Mix well. Mix in Rice Krispies. Form into 1 inch balls, flatten with bottom of glass. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: peanut brownie pie a la mode
directions: Melt chocolate and cool. Cream the softened butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Stir in chocolate and vanilla. Add flour and mix well. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually fold egg whites and peanuts into chocolate batter.
Spread batter into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into wedges and top with scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: crab st. jacques
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine.
Blend in cornstarch. Add milk, wine and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Blend in seasonings.
Add crab and heat through.
Divide between 2 scallop shells or individual au gratin dishes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese.
Broil 3 to 5 inches from heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Beat eggs; add melted oleo, pumpkin, vanilla and lemon.
Mix well.
Add sugar and flour.
Add nuts; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured sheet cake pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 400° or until brown.
Make sure it is cold before trying to cut into squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: In frying pan cook mushrooms, onions and garlic in butter until onions are lightly browned.
Add oregano, parsley and lemon juice.
Lay fillets flat in baking dish (closely fit).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Divide stuffing into 4 equal parts and lay over fillets.
Place 4 other fillets on top and sprinkle with additional lemon juice and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan mix milk, vanilla, sugar, salt and margarine.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Remove from heat.
Separate eggs; set whites aside in a grease-free bowl. Maintain them at room temperature.
Slowly add half of the heated liquid to the egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Pour yolks back into remainder of the heated mixture.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water and add to the milk/egg mixture to boiling.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until cool.
Add peanut butter to the cooled pudding. Mix well and pour into a cooled, baked pie crust.

title: fried shrimp
directions: In medium bowl,
beat
egg,
adding evaporated milk and water. Split each
shrimp
two-thirds
of its length.
Season generously with the
salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Dip each shrimp in the egg
batter,
then
roll
in
flour,
dip in egg batter again and roll in bread crumbs.
Heat oil in a deep fat fryer to 375° and fry
for
to
minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot with your favorite sauce.

title: oven crusty fish
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
If
using
whole corn flakes, crush into fine crumbs and set
aside.
Cut fish into serving pieces (allow 1/4 pound per
serving).
Combine
milk
and salt.
Dip fish in milk, then in
crumbs.
Arrange
on
well oiled baking sheet or shallow pan.
Sprinkle fish with vegetable oil.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° about 20 minutes or until tender.

title: low-fat spiced pork and apple skillet dinner
directions: Partially freeze pork and slice thin.
Combine next 4 ingredients and set aside.
Combine spices; add pork and toss well.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in skillet; add pork and brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from skillet and reserve drippings in skillet.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and apples to skillet.
Stir constantly until apples are browned.
Return pork to skillet.
Add pineapple tidbits and reserved apple juice mixture.
Stir constantly 2 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: sid's stuffed clams
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into clam shells and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot and brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In large saucepan, bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir for a few minutes to cool slightly.
Add oats and pecans.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Let cool and harden.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish put broccoli in, then cooked, cut up chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Bake 35 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan or 40 minutes for 2-quart deep dish at 350°.

title: stuffed breast of possum
directions: Debone and pound flat possum breast.
Press garlic mixed with olive oil and rub on upper side of breast.
Layer thinly on breast Mozzarella cheese, Prosciutto ham, sauteed peppers, onions, brown sausage or scrapple.
Fold over and seal edge by sewing together with half stitches using meat twine.
Place 1-inch of rock salt in large clay roasting pot.
Place stuffed breast on salt.
Fill pot and bake at 500° for 1 hour.
Three more hours at 300°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into a greased and floured angel food pan (or spray pan with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: horseradish and parsley dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with raw veggies or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: flo's chicken supreme
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and place in a greased 2-quart casserole. Cover this with the cheese and then the noodles.
Bake until bubbly, about 25 minutes in oven set at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries until berries break apart.
Add sliced bananas and chopped pecans. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Next, spread sour cream over first mixture and pour remaining 1/2 of jello on top.
Place in refrigerator to jell entire mixture.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain and add pizza sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour pizza mixture in glass dish. Top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: basic potpourri
directions: Potpourri ingredients should be placed in tightly closed glass container and allowed to set for 2 to 4 weeks.
Shake the container daily.

title: baker's sweet chocolate igloo dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar, salt and milk in medium saucepan.
Add Baker's German's sweet chocolate.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is completely melted.
Blend mixture well with eggbeater.
Add small amount of hot mixture to 3 slightly beaten egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Gradually add remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to saucepan and cook over low heat until mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Pour into a large bowl and chill until partially thickened.
Stir in vanilla.

title: picante sauce
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Lower fire and simmer slowly, covered, about 20 minutes.
Use big pot.
Stir very often.
Pour into hot jars.
Makes 12 to 14 pints.
Water bath 10 minutes if you plan to keep it more than 4 months.

title: spaghetti shrimp salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 2 or 3 pieces.
Boil for 15 minutes or until done.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
When cold, add chopped pepper, shrimp and onion.
Combine vinegar, sugar, dry broth seasoning and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add to spaghetti and mix thoroughly.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Add next 6 ingredients, then add yeast mixture.
Add flour to form stiff dough. Cover to rise to double.
Stir down. Turn into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or 8-inch round pan. Let rise 30 to 40 minutes until light.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef until brown and drain. Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Stir.
Stir in taco seasoning mix (dry), tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomato and shredded lettuce.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: *I cook the chicken in crock-pot on high for 4 hours.
No water added.
Or cook overnight if chicken is frozen.

title: chorizo tortilla casserole
directions: Cover and bake in a 350° oven about 50 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Garnish with fresh cilantro or parsley if desired. Servings:

title: hash brown potato salad
directions: Place bacon in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. Add onions to the drippings. Cover and microwave on High for 1 minute. Add the potatoes. Cover and cook on High for 10 minutes, stirring several times. Add vinegar, celery salt and bacon. Toss. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cheesy cupcakes
directions: Make sure cream cheese is soft, then beat all ingredients until nice and smooth.
Use foil cupcake liners.
Place a Nilla wafer in liner.
Fill liner about 3/4 way.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
You may also use any flavor jelly.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers of apple mixture and sweet potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top off with marshmallows.
Heat until slightly brown.

title: cheesy potatoes in a crock-pot
directions: Let potatoes come to a full boil.
Pour off water.
Put into crock-pot on low.
Add cheese, soup and margarine.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once or twice while cooking.
A few red and green peppers can be added for color.

title: molded salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Let chill.
Add milk and let begin to set.
Add remainder of the ingredients and put in your favorite mold.
Serves 8.

title: tuna sandwich
directions: Mix all together.
Put on hamburger buns; wrap each bun in foil.
Place in oven and bake at 300° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Good to keep in refrigerator and make a sandwich when you would like one.
Good lunch with a cup of soup.

title: flossie johnson's bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Also, slice onions.
Cut up peppers.
Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly.

title: cheese danish
directions: Or use your favorite glaze or icing.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package. Pour into prepared loaf pan. Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar and eggs.
Spoon over top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Test for doneness; toothpick should be clean when cake is done.
Garnish with fresh fruit and powdered sugar, if desired.

title: rhubarb torte(sugar-free)
directions: Cook rhubarb in microwave (covered) for 6 minutes on High. Stir and continue to cook 6 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Stir in the Jell-O; cool.

title: cajun mistakes
directions: Cook meat until done; drain.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Mix well.
Spread on party rye or pumpernickel.
Place on cookie sheet; freeze.
When frozen, put into plastic bags.
When ready to use, place in 400° oven until bubbly.

title: apple cream coffee cake
directions: Combine walnuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; beat until blended.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Spread half of batter in greased 9-inch tube pan.
Top with 1 apple and half of walnut mixture.
Top with rest of batter and add 1 sliced apple and remaining walnut mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Let stand on wire rack for 30 minutes and remove to serving plate.

title: picante shrimp
directions: Heat oil.
Saute garlic.
Slice peppers and mushrooms.
Cut up or dice tomatoes.
Add peppers, tomatoes and mushrooms to garlic and saute a few minutes.
Add basil, picante sauce and shrimp.
Cook just until shrimp is done.
Add cooked rigatoni and freshly grated Parmesan cheese; toss and serve.
Seres 2.

title: raisin nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, shortening and buttermilk.
Beat 2 minutes and then add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake until cake tests done.
Cool.
Spread with Egyptian filling.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for oblong cake.

title: punch
directions: Stir together boiling water and jello until dissolved.
Stir together sugar and warm water.
Add cold water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice; freeze.
Let thaw about 2 hours.
Add 7-Up.

title: macaroni chicken salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add water and shortening. Dough will be soft.
Knead it together quickly and lightly until smooth and elastic.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled, about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.

title: teri's catheral fudge
directions: Melt and cool butter and chocolate chips.
Add chopped nuts, eggs and colored marshmallows.
Set 1/2 hour and make 2 logs. Roll on wax paper covered with chopped nuts.
Slice and refrigerate at least 8 to 12 hours.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Melt butter; add garlic salt.
Brush on biscuits after baking.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
May need to add flour to make thick batter.
Form into small balls (approximately 1 teaspoon) and drop into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam, then lightly flour.
In mixing bowl, thoroughly cream first 3 ingredients.
Stir in next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Core and chop apples into small pieces; leave skins on.
Fold apples and nuts into mixture.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: arroz con pollo casserole
directions: Cook flour and garlic in oil over low heat, stirring constantly, until flour is browned.
Stir in chili powder. Gradually add milk, broth, picante sauce, cumin and oregano.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Add process cheese spread; stir until melted.
Keep warm.
Spoon 2 cups rice onto bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; top with half the chicken.
Spoon 1 cup sauce mixture evenly over chicken; top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Top with remaining rice and chicken.
Spoon remaining sauce evenly over chicken.
Cover with remaining shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Top with sour cream and olives, as desired.
Serve with additional picante sauce. Yields 8 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and let set 24 hours before serving.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Drain tomatoes; reserve liquid.
Heat the liquid to boiling. Add bouillon cube until dissolved.
Add tomatoes, onion, celery, salt and bread cubes.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Dab top with butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: taco quiche
directions: In a large skillet, cook the beef, onion, green pepper and taco seasoning over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Spread into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with the shredded cheese. In a bowl, combine the Bisquick mix, eggs and milk. Pour over the cheese. Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serves 4-6 people.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir zucchini, mushrooms and onion in butter over medium heat until tender.
Place remaining ingredients in blender or food processor; cover and blend until smooth.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch quiche or pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hidden valley snack crackers
directions: Mix together in Ziploc bag. Turn several times for 24 hours.

title: apricot candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Add chopped dried apricots and chopped pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and let harden.
Cut or break apart in bite-sized pieces and store in container.

title: spam fettucine primavera
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in milk, broth and basil; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened and keep warm.
Cook fettucine according to package directions; drain and return to saucepan. Stir in Spam, vegetables and sauce.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows; cool.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add pineapple and nuts.
This should all be a mold of your choice.
Then refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls flat on a cookie sheet, pinching seams together, forming crust.
Bake crescent roll crust according to package instructions, then cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread this mixture over crust. Layer vegetables on top.
Cover with wax paper and gently press vegetables into cream cheese mixture.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Remove wax paper and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of pizza.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix pineapple juice, sugar and Jell-O.
Heat until sugar and Jell-O dissolve.
Put in refrigerator until syrupy.
Whip can of icy Pet milk and gradually add syrupy mixture.
Line 2 pie dishes with vanilla wafers; slowly pour mixture over wafers.
Refrigerate. Can use lime Jell-O.
Makes 2 pies.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add peanuts and cook until mixture turns dark.
Remove from heat. Add baking soda, salt and vinegar.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet or foil pie plates.
Cool and break in pieces.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash tomatoes and peppers.
Cut top to use as caps after stuffing.
Scoop out seeds and some of the pulp.
Brown onions in oil and pulp from tomatoes.
Parboil the peppers.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat water, vinegar and sugar together until sugar is dissolved (stirring).
Add beets to pan, stir well and remove from heat.
Store in container in refrigerator.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and corn meal.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each addition. Add liquids, mix well.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until halfway done, about 4 minutes; drain.
Add cream, butter, garlic, tomato sauce and broccoli; bring to a boil over medium heat, about 4 to 5 minutes. When noodles are done, stir in mushrooms to heat.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.

title: offshore gumbo
directions: Cook whole chicken until it comes off the bone and leave in water.
Add shrimp and all seasons and bring to boil and serve with rice and crackers.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain well. Mix the rest of the ingredients and add to cooked broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
I use an 8-inch square one.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Sprinkle a little paprika on the crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: In 9 X 13 pan, melt margarine. Crush Ritz crackers. Place on top of melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool. Mix pudding and milk well until thick. Blend in ice cream. Pour over top of cooled crust. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with grated Heath bar. Store in freezer.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. "This cake is even better the second day."

title: cheesy spaghetti
directions: Mix and pour into Pammed baker.
Bake until bubbly and all cheese melted.
Works great in a microwave, just stir about halfway through cook time.

title: granola bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, honey, vanilla, oil and water.
Heat to boiling point and cool.
Then add the remaining dry ingredients. Pat into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool overnight.
Cut into 16 bars with 210 calories each.

title: seafood scampi(serves 4)
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium-high heat.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add remaining Scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: pesto
directions: Combine all but oil and cheeses in a food processor and process until smooth, adding olive oil gradually.
Stir in cheeses and taste for balance and consistency, adding more cheese or olive oil and adjusting garlic to your taste.
More olive oil is necessary to make a sauce for pasta, less for pesto to top crackers and cream cheese.
Mix pesto with mayonnaise, yogurt or sour cream for a dip. Pesto is wonderful swirled in tomato, vegetable or minestrone soup.

title: ketchup
directions: Mix well in blender or food blender.
Ready to use.

title: burger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in
salted water until tender.
Brown meat and onion; add soup and
milk
to
meat.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, first noodles, then
meat mixture, then sliced olives and cheese. Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish or deep pie plate and set aside.
Combine flour and remaining sugar.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with a big scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: rice hotel - rice pudding
directions: You will need 8 custard cups.

title: dilly dip
directions: Use Spice Islands spices if available; if not, I have used Schilling.
Mix together and serve.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put in bread cubes.
Top with cheese. Add broccoli, meat and optionals.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Put enough milk to dissolve marshmallows.
Put in container and finish filling with milk.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Wash, peel and cut carrots into 2-inch strips.
Cook in salt water until just tender; drain and cool.
Combine soup, sugar, vinegar, salad oil and dry mustard in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour over carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients and blend well. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, margarine, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: great chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients. Pour over chicken wings. Marinate 3 to 4 hours. Drain. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl,
cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
While beating add water mixed with soda, salt and vanilla.
Blend in	the
mixer
about half the flour, stopping when mixer begins
to
feel
overloaded.
Transfer to largest bowl; mix in rest of
flour and oatmeal, preferably by hand.
If using raisins,
chocolate
chips and nuts, work them in last. Form into 5 or 6
rolls, 1 1/2 to 2-inches in diameter, depending on how large
you
like your cookies.
Store in refrigerator overnight or freeze for a couple of hours to make them easier to slice.
Slice
cookies
1/4-inch thick and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries into pan and level. Pour in pineapple then spread yellow cake mix out.
Melt and sprinkle margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top.
Bake until crunchy on top.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: veal supreme
directions: Brown veal in butter and remove to large casserole.
Saute mushrooms, onion, zucchini and tomato in same pan.
Add to meat in casserole.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and sherry.
Pour over meat.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin pecan muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Stir in mayonnaise; add the pumpkin and pecans.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir flour mixture into pumpkin mixture.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups (fill cups full).
Sprinkle tops with additional chopped pecans if desired.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes before removing from the pan.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler or microwave.
Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to set.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix the oil, pecans, salt and pepper in a medium sized mixing bowl.
Turn into a shallow baking pan and roast until done, about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl and add fruit slices and maraschino cherries if desired.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cranberry sauce(low calorie; no fat)
directions: Place rinsed cranberries in a large saucepan with remaining ingredients.
Simmer over very low heat, just until cranberries pop open.
Cool.
Chill before serving.
Makes 12 servings, 60 calories each.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir in broccoli mixture, instant bouillon, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat just to boiling. Stir in half and half.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve with grated cheese, if desired.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla until well blended. Add milk, then let stand until all foam disappears.
Then pour into deep 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and a little more nutmeg.
Bake at 400° until it starts to brown, about 20 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and bake until custard is set. Time approximately 1 hour.
Don't overbake custard.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: In large mixer bowl beat 1 cup margarine; add about 1/2 flour, all the brown sugar, eggs, 2 teaspoons of the vanilla and baking soda.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour. Stir in oats.

title: chicken breasts baked in wine
directions: Place chicken breasts in an open baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt, pepper, onion, mustard and parsley.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or more.
When nearly done, add wine and baste with juices in pan. Do not overcook.
This is delicious with rice.

title: fruit mix
directions: May use all juice or drain fruit according to your taste.

title: food for the gods
directions: Combine sugar, dates, pecans, cracker crumbs and egg; stir until blended.
Spread very thin on a very lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° until slightly browned and crisp.
Check frequently; needs to be done only enough to crumble.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: carob kisses
directions: Mix
all ingredients except carob chips to form kisses. Melt chips in double boiler.
Dip candy pieces into carob and refrigerate.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix well!
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed for pie using 1 1/2 cups milk. Blend in the whipped topping. Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 hours. Arrange strawberries on filling and garnish with more whipped topping.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Add egg to bread crumbs in large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients to bread crumbs/egg mixture, except beef and bouillon.
Add beef and bouillon; mix well and turn into meatloaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: amaretto pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and salt, alternating with creamer.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased, floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Beat in molasses and water.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Combine with first mixture to form a stiff dough.

title: broccoli-orange salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and pecans in a bowl and set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in the order given; bake in a greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for an hour or until tests done.
It will pull away from the sides of the pan when done.
Cool for a few minutes and then remove from pan.

title: banana split salad
directions: Beat together powdered sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Cut bananas lengthwise.
Then begin layering everything starting with graham crackers, then sugar mixture, bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip; top with nuts and cherries.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: *Green chilies will work.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients just enough to blend.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan and bake in hot oven at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: margie's ginger and garlic chicken and rice
directions: Pour chicken broth over breasts.
Mix vinegar and other ingredients and stir into chicken breast mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot spicy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cracker crumbs) together.
Dip chicken in dressing mix; then roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on a greased baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until done at 425°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Use with chicken, pork or beef.

title: popovers
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs and butter; beat slightly. Gradually beat in milk, flour and salt.
Pour batter into 10 well-oiled custard cups.
Place cups on baking sheet.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350° or until firm and brown.
Makes 10 popovers.

title: easy hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion soup mix and enough water to cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add mixed vegetables and tomato juice.
Simmer another 10 minutes and serve.

title: posole stew
directions: Soak posole overnight in water.
Rinse soaked posole with fresh water, set aside.
Put tomatoes and chiles in a large pot. Dissolve bouillon in 2 cups hot water, add to pot.
Put posole and rest of ingredients in pot.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stew is ready when posole in tender.
A can of cooked hominy can be substituted for the posole to make this dish much quicker.
Do not drain the hominy.

title: angel food
directions: Mix well. Bake in 9 x 13 pan (do not grease or flour). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Fat-free.

title: instant fruit cake
directions: Omit water and add instead 1/2 ounce vanilla and 1/2 ounce lemon flavoring.
